{"title_page": "J.P. Morgan Cazenove", "text_new": "{{notability|date=March 2020}}\n'''JPMorgan Cazenove''' is an investment bank focused on [[mergers & acquisitions]], [[private placement agent|debt and equity placements]] and equity research and distribution based in the [[UK]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=20332795|publisher=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]|title=Company Overview of J.P. Morgan Cazenove Limited|date=October 26, 2015 }}</ref> The firm has approximately 900 employees.\n\nThe firm was originally established as a joint venture between [[JPMorgan Chase|JPMorgan]] and [[Cazenove (stock broker)|Cazenove]] founded in 2004 and headquartered in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2014/11/06/j-p-morgans-bet-on-cazenove-still-bearing-fruit/|publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|author=Emily Glazer|title=J.P. Morgan\u2019s Bet on Cazenove Still Bearing Fruit |date=December 12, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 JPMorgan bought Cazenove out, and it is now a wholly owned subsidiary of JPMorgan.\n\n==See also==\n*[[JPMorgan Chase]]\n*[[Cazenove (stock broker)|Cazenove]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.jpmorgancazenove.com/ J.P. Morgan Cazenove] (company website)\n\n{{JPMorgan Chase}}\n{{Investment banks}}\n\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Banks established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Investment banks]]\n[[Category:JPMorgan Chase]]\n\n\n{{finance-company-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{notability|date=March 2020}}\n'''JPMorgan Cazenove''' is a investment bank focused on [[mergers & acquisitions]], [[private placement agent|debt and equity placements]] and equity research and distribution based in the [[UK]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=20332795|publisher=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]|title=Company Overview of J.P. Morgan Cazenove Limited|date=October 26, 2015 }}</ref> The firm has approximately 900 employees.\n\nThe firm was originally established as a joint venture between [[JPMorgan Chase|JPMorgan]] and [[Cazenove (stock broker)|Cazenove]] founded in 2004 and headquartered in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2014/11/06/j-p-morgans-bet-on-cazenove-still-bearing-fruit/|publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|author=Emily Glazer|title=J.P. Morgan\u2019s Bet on Cazenove Still Bearing Fruit |date=December 12, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 JPMorgan bought Cazenove out, and it is now a wholly owned subsidiary of JPMorgan. \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[JPMorgan Chase]]\n*[[Cazenove (stock broker)|Cazenove]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.jpmorgancazenove.com/ J.P. Morgan Cazenove] (company website)\n\n\n{{JPMorgan Chase}}\n{{Investment banks}}\n\n{{finance-company-stub}}\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Banks established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Investment banks]]\n[[Category:JPMorgan Chase]]\n", "name_user": "Nat965", "label": "safe", "comment": "ApplyGen fix(es),typo(s) fixed: a investment \u2192 an investment", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J.P._Morgan_Cazenove"}
{"title_page": "Bertelsmann Stiftung", "text_new": "{{Use American English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| logo = Bertelsmann Stiftung Logo.png\n| logo_alt = Logo of the Bertelsmann Stiftung\n| formation = {{start date and age|1977}}<ref>{{cite news|language=de|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung neu organisiert|newspaper=B\u00f6rsen-Zeitung|date={{date|2004-07-21|mdy}}|page=11}}</ref>\n| key_people = {{ublist|[[J\u00f6rg Dr\u00e4ger]]|[[Brigitte Mohn]]|[[Liz Mohn]]}}\n| name = Bertelsmann Stiftung\n| named_after = [[Carl Bertelsmann]]\n| logo_size = 200px\n| founder = [[Reinhard Mohn]]<ref>{{cite news|language=de|title=Im Auftrag des Patriarchen: Bertelsmann Stiftung erinnert an Reinhard Mohn|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische|date={{date|2010-05-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n| location = [[G\u00fctersloh]], [[Germany]]\n| additional_location = [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]\n| additional_location2 = [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]]\n| revenue = {{increase}} [[Euro|\u20ac]]130.0 [[million]]<ref name=\"Finanzen\" />\n| revenue_year = 2019\n| expenses = {{increase}} \u20ac90.5 million<ref name=\"Finanzen\" />\n| expenses_year = 2019\n| endowment = \u20ac619.5 million<ref name=\"Finanzen\" />\n| endowment_year = 2019\n| staff = 386<ref name=\"Finanzen\" />\n| staff_year = 2019\n| main_organ = Exective Board (Vorstand)\n| subsidiaries = {{ublist|Fundaci\u00f3n Bertelsmann|Bertelsmann Foundation}}\n| motto = \"Inspiring people. Shaping the future. Participating in a globalized world.\"<ref>{{cite web|language=en|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/about-us/what-motivates-us/our-mission/|title=Mission Statement: Our Core Principles|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|access-date={{date|2017-05-31|mdy}}}}</ref>\n| website = {{URL|bertelsmann-stiftung.de}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Bertelsmann_Stiftung_2007-01.jpg|thumb|Headquarters of the Bertelsmann Stiftung in G\u00fctersloh (2007)]]\n\nThe '''Bertelsmann Stiftung''' is an independent [[Foundation (nonprofit)|foundation]] under private law, based in [[G\u00fctersloh]], Germany. It was founded in 1977 by [[Reinhard Mohn]] as the result of social, corporate and fiscal considerations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/unternehmen/bertelsmann-patriarch-mohn-tod-eines-wirtschaftsweisen-a-653111.html|title=Tod eines Wirtschaftsweisen|date={{date|2009-10-04|mdy}}|website=Spiegel Online|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/ueber-uns/was-uns-bewegt/motive-des-stifters/|title=Von der Welt lernen: Warum Reinhard Mohn die Bertelsmann Stiftung gr\u00fcndete|website=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2015-11-24|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.taz.de/!5137745/|title=Die Methode Bertelsmann: Eine Stiftung regiert das Land|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|website=Die Tageszeitung|language=de|access-date={{date|2015-10-01|mdy}}|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Erfolgsfaktor Unternehmenskultur: Mit kulturbewusstem Management Unternehmensziele erreichen und Identifikation schaffen|publisher=Springer Verlag|year=2004|isbn=978-3-322-82623-7|location=Wiesbaden|page=275|language=de|author=Sonja A. Sackmann}}</ref> As the Bertelsmann Stiftung itself has put it, the foundation promotes \"reform processes\" and \"the principles of entrepreneurial activity\" to build a \"future-oriented society.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.freitag.de/autoren/der-freitag/die-tonangeber|title=Die Tonangeber|date={{date|2006-06-16|mdy}}|website=Der Freitag|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nSince 1993, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has held the majority of capital shares in the [[Bertelsmann|Bertelsmann Group]].<ref name=\"1993-10-14\"/> It holds 80.9% together with the Reinhard Mohn Stiftung and the BVG Stiftung but has no voting rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann.de/unternehmen/aktionaere/|title=Aktion\u00e4rsstruktur|publisher=Bertelsmann|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-12|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Reinhard_Mohn_Portrait_2008.jpg|thumb|Reinhard Mohn (2008)]]\n\n=== Establishment of the foundation ===\nAt the end of the 1970s, there were discussions concerning who would follow Reinhard Mohn as chairman of Bertelsmann.<ref>{{cite book|title=175 Jahre Bertelsmann: Eine Zukunftsgeschichte|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-570-10175-9|location=M\u00fcnchen|pages=44\u201345|language=de}}</ref> Against this background and because he believed that the state must be able to count on its citizens' willingness to assume responsibility and take the initiative, Mohn founded the Bertelsmann Stiftung on February 8, 1977.<ref name=\"Chronicle\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/about-us/who-we-are/chronicle/|title=Chronicle|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=en|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> It was officially approved by the authorities on March 14, 1977.<ref>{{cite book|title=Die Mohns \u2013 Vom Provinzbuchh\u00e4ndler zum Weltkonzern / Die Familie hinter Bertelsmann|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2004|isbn=978-3-593-41565-9|location=Frankfurt am Main|page=291|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung was initially endowed with 100,000 [[Deutsche Mark]]s in capital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geschichte.nrw.de/artikel.php?artikel%5Bid%5D=866|title=Wettbewerb und b\u00fcrgerschaftliches Engagement|publisher=Landeszentrale f\u00fcr politische Bildung Nordrhein-Westfalen|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303201603/http://www.geschichte.nrw.de/artikel.php?artikel%5Bid%5D=866|archive-date=March 3, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Die Stadtbibliothek G\u00fctersloh GmbH: Kooperationsversuch zwischen Medienunternehmen und Kommune|publisher=Harrassowitz Verlag|year=1983|isbn=3-447-02370-8|location=Wiesbaden|page=48|language=de}}</ref> About two years later it began its work.\n\n=== Building the foundation's work ===\nIn 1979, Hans-Dieter Weger was appointed the first managing director. He developed the concept of an operational foundation that develops and oversees its own projects.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ein Anstifter des Guten|date={{date|2004-09-16|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> One of the Bertelsmann Stiftung's first activities was the [[Baseline Study|baseline study]] \"Kommunikationsverhalten und Buch\" (Communication Behavior and the Book), which was prepared in cooperation with [[Infratest dimap|Infratest]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kommunikationsverhalten und Buch: Endbericht|publisher=Infratest|year=1978|location=M\u00fcnchen|language=de|editor=Bodo Franzmann}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung and the Bertelsmann Group also provided support for&nbsp;the construction of the G\u00fctersloh municipal&nbsp;library.<ref>{{cite book|title=Die Stadtbibliothek G\u00fctersloh GmbH: Kooperationsversuch zwischen Medienunternehmen und Kommune|publisher=Harrassowitz Verlag|year=1983|isbn=3-447-02370-8|location=Wiesbaden|page=50|language=de}}</ref>\n\nIn 1982, the Bertelsmann Stiftung presented its first public report of its activities. In the report's foreword, [[Karl Carstens]], [[President of Germany|president of the Federal Republic of Germany]], praised the \"achievement of foundations in the public sphere.\"<ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|page=49|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref> In the meantime, the Bertelsmann Stiftung had come to play a central role in Reinhard Mohn's sociopolitical activities.<ref>{{cite news|title=Personalien|date={{date|1986-06-27|mdy}}|page=24|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> Mohn functioned as the foundation's sole executive and was supported by a newly created advisory board from 1983 onwards. In addition to Reinhard Mohn and Hans-Dieter Weger, the board's members were&nbsp;[[Kurt Biedenkopf]], [[Gerd Bucerius]], Friedhelm Farthmann and Eberhard Witte.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> In 1985, a publishing house was founded as part of the foundation in order to handle the growing number of publications. Verlag Bertelsmann Stiftung still exists today.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adb-online.de/|title=Profilansicht: Verlag Bertelsmann Stiftung|website=Adressbuch f\u00fcr den deutschsprachigen Buchhandel|publisher=Marketing- und Verlagsservice des Buchhandels|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nIn 1988, the Bertelsmann Stiftung awarded the Carl Bertelsmann Prize (now known as the Reinhard Mohn Prize) for the first time. The recipients were employer organizations and trade unions in the construction, chemistry and metalworking industries.<ref>{{cite news|title=Carl-Bertelsmann-Preis|date={{date|1988-04-18|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> Today, the award continues to honor internationally renowned figures&nbsp;who have developed pioneering solutions to social and political challenges.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.n-tv.de/politik/Schwab-erhaelt-Reinhard-Mohn-Preis-article17960896.html|title=Weitblick und Geschick: Schwab erh\u00e4lt Reinhard-Mohn-Preis|date={{date|2016-06-16|mdy}}|website=n-tv|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-12|mdy}}}}</ref> In addition to working in Germany, the Bertelsmann Stiftung initiated several international projects in the 1980s,<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> such as the \"Kulturraum Europa\" (European Culture Space).<ref>{{cite news|title=Einf\u00fchrung und Chronologie des Projekts Kulturraum Europa|year=2011|location=G\u00fctersloh|language=de|author=Kai Franke|newspaper=Chronik der Bertelsmann Stiftung}}</ref> Further examples include a program at the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] and the construction of the Biblioteca Can Torr\u00f3 in [[Alc\u00fadia]] on the island of Majorca.<ref>{{cite book|title=Schl\u00fcsselmomente: Erfahrungen eines engagierten Lebens|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2011|isbn=978-3-641-07123-3|location=M\u00fcnchen|page=20|language=de|author=Liz Mohn}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Alcudia macht Reinhard Mohn zum Ehrenb\u00fcrger|date={{date|2005-09-14|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gorbatschow_in_G\u00fctersloh_1992.jpg|thumb|Mikhail Gorbachev, Reinhard Mohn and Liz Mohn in the foyer of the Bertelsmann Stiftung (1992)]]\nKurt Biedenkopf was elected as the first chairman of the advisory board in 1987,<ref>{{cite news|title=Personalien|date={{date|1987-09-11|mdy}}|page=22|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> and Reinhard Mohn himself took over this position in 1990.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> Horst Teltschik then joined the foundation, a development that received a great deal of media attention. The former foreign policy adviser to [[Helmut Kohl]] became managing director of the Bertelsmann Stiftung in early 1991 and began focusing on the foundation's internationalization.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kohls Kopf bei Bertelsmann|date={{date|1990-12-06|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Teltschik will Profil der Bertelsmann Stiftung sch\u00e4rfen|date={{date|1991-02-06|mdy}}|page=9|language=de|newspaper=Bonner General-Anzeiger}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung: Teltschik setzt auf Expertenseminare und Projektf\u00f6rderung. Arbeit soll auf neue L\u00e4nder ausgedehnt und Aktuelles schneller umgesetzt werden|date={{date|1991-02-06|mdy}}|page=7|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> At the end of the 1980s, the Bertelsmann Stiftung offices were built&nbsp;opposite the Bertelsmann corporate&nbsp;headquarters.<ref name=\"Gerkan, Mang und Partner\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gmp-architekten.de/projekte/carl-bertelsmann-stiftung.html|title=Projekte|publisher=Gerkan, Marg und Partner|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/about-us/who-we-are/offices/|title=Offices|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=en|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] was a guest during his first trip to Germany after the demise&nbsp;of the [[Soviet Union]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-13855374.html|title=Deutlich darunter|date={{date|1992-03-09|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Der Spiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Niemand wird f\u00fcr uns die Probleme l\u00f6sen k\u00f6nnen|date={{date|1992-03-11|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref>\n\n=== Transferring the majority interest ===\nIn addition to Reinhard Mohn, Ulrich Saxer and Werner Weidenfeld were appointed to the Bertelsmann Stiftung [[executive board]] in 1993. New management was also hired.<ref name=\"1993-05-28\">{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung: Mohn k\u00fcndigt deutliche Etataufstockung f\u00fcr 1993/94 an; Forschungsprogramm soll Reform der sozialen Marktwirtschaft ausloten|date={{date|1993-05-28|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> In the same year, Reinhard Mohn transferred the majority of the capital shares in the&nbsp;Bertelsmann Group to the foundation, a move intended to ensure continuity at the company.<ref>{{cite book|title=175 Jahre Bertelsmann: Eine Zukunftsgeschichte|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-570-10175-9|location=M\u00fcnchen|pages=274\u2013276|language=de}}</ref> The transaction increased the foundation's stake in the company from 21.3% to 68.8%,<ref name=\"1993-10-14\" /><ref name=\"1993-05-28\" /> being the largest [[shareholder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.n-tv.de/wirtschaft/Bertelsmann-bewahrt-Tradition-article534278.html|title=Nach dem Tod von Reinhard Mohn: Bertelsmann bewahrt Tradition|date={{date|2009-10-05|mdy}}|website=n-tv|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> In the 1993 transfer agreement, however, shareholdings and voting rights were strictly separated, so that the foundation cannot exercise any significant influence on the Bertelsmann Group,<ref name=\"1993-10-14\">{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann geh\u00f6rt jetzt mehrheitlich der Stiftung|date={{date|1993-10-14|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=Deutscher Drucker}}</ref> which is still largely controlled by the Mohn family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann.de/unternehmen/aktionaere/|title=Aktion\u00e4rsstruktur|publisher=Bertelsmann|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/unternehmen/it-medien/bertelsmann-medienmonarchie-aus-guetersloh/3818956.html|title=Medienmonarchie aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2011-01-30|mdy}}|website=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> As the foundation receives dividends for its holdings in the company, the transfer of shares resulted in a significant increase in the organization's budget.<ref name=\"1993-05-28\" />\n\n=== Restructuring of governance boards ===\nIn 1998, Reinhard Mohn stepped down from his leading role at the Bertelsmann Stiftung. Mark W\u00f6ssner was first elected chairman of the executive board, and, a year later, chairman of the advisory board.<ref>{{cite news|title=Der Leitwolf verl\u00e4\u00dft das Rudel|date={{date|1998-09-24|mdy}}|page=14|language=de|author=Thomas Hoffmann|newspaper=Horizont}}</ref> After W\u00f6ssner's departure in 2000, the foundation's governance structure changed again:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tagesspiegel.de/wirtschaft/die-komplizierte-romanze-der-liz-mohn/472428.html|title=Die komplizierte Romanze der Liz Mohn|date={{date|2003-12-08|mdy}}|website=Der Tagesspiegel|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Matthew Karnitschnig}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mohn stellt die Weichen|date={{date|2000-09-29|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Allgemeine Zeitung}}</ref> the executive board was replaced by an executive committee and the advisory board was replaced by a board of trustees.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung erh\u00e4lt neue F\u00fchrungsstruktur|date={{date|2009-09-29|mdy}}|page=28|language=de|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref> As an interim step, at the end of 2000 Reinhard Mohn became chairman of both the executive committee and the board of trustees, until [[Gunter Thielen]] succeeded him in both positions in mid-2001.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mohn wird Pr\u00e4sident der Bertelsmann Stiftung / Im Juli 2002 soll Gunter Thielen das Amt \u00fcbernehmen|date={{date|2000-09-29|mdy}}|page=17|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Der Patriarch zieht sich zur\u00fcck|date={{date|2001-08-05|mdy}}|page=18|language=de|newspaper=Berliner Zeitung}}</ref> With this step, Reinhard Mohn gave up all previous management functions, remaining only a member of the board of trustees.<ref>{{cite news|title=Der Patriarch schont die Kr\u00e4fte|date={{date|2001-08-25|mdy}}|page=31|language=de|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Reinhard Mohn tritt ab|date={{date|2001-08-25|mdy}}|page=25|language=de|newspaper=Bonner General-Anzeiger}}</ref>\n\n{{ill|Heribert Meffert|de}} succeeded Gunter Thielen in 2002 and continued to lead the Bertelsmann Stiftung until 2005.<ref>{{cite news|title=Marketing-Papst \u00fcbernimmt Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2002-08-10|mdy}}|page=27|language=de|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Meffert verl\u00e4sst Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2005-06-17|mdy}}|page=20|language=de|author=Thomas Kn\u00fcwer, Hans-Peter Siebenhaar|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> During his tenure, the executive committee became an executive board once again;<ref>{{cite news|title=Der Stifter als Bauherr|date={{date|2004-07-20|mdy}}|language=de|author=Stefan Brams|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> the goal was to strengthen corporate governance by promoting greater transparency and independence.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wir wollen keine geheimen Ministerien sein|date={{date|2005-04-29|mdy}}|language=de|author=Marc Beise, Hans-J\u00fcrgen Jakobs|newspaper=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung}}</ref> After Meffert left the foundation, it was jointly led by board chairs [[Liz Mohn]] and Johannes Meier.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/karriere/a-360818.html|title=Meffert geht fr\u00fcher|date={{date|2005-06-16|mdy}}|website=Manager Magazin|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> In 2008, Gunter Thielen returned to the Bertelsmann Stiftung as chairman of the executive board.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/karriere/a-309347.html|title=Thielen wird Stiftungsleiter|date={{date|2004-07-19|mdy}}|website=Manager Magazin|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.horizont.net/medien/nachrichten/-Gunter-Thielen-geht-zurueck-zur-Bertelsmann-Stiftung-73885|title=Gunter Thielen geht zur\u00fcck zur Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2008-01-03|mdy}}|website=Horizont|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-01|mdy}}}}</ref> Since 2012, the foundation has been led by [[Aart de Geus|Aart De Geus]], former Dutch minister of labor and social affairs.<ref>{{cite news|title=Regierungswechsel in G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2012-08-04|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Ab August Chef der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2012-05-03|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|author=David Hein|newspaper=Horizont}}</ref> Following his retirement at the end of 2019, it was announced that [[Ralph Heck]] would take over as chairman of the executive board in mid-2020.<ref>{{cite web|language=de|url=https://www.welt.de/regionales/nrw/article201310968/Neuer-Chef-fuer-Bertelsmann-Stiftung-Heck-loest-De-Geus-ab.html|title=Neuer Chef f\u00fcr Bertelsmann-Stiftung: Heck l\u00f6st De Geus ab|website=Welt Online|date={{date|2019-10-02|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2020-01-31|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n== Organization ==\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung is an independent foundation under private law, according to the laws governing foundations in the state of [[North Rhine-Westphalia]].<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> It is an unrestricted legal entity, which, internally and externally, must exclusively pursue the mission defined in its bylaws.<ref>{{cite book|title=Praxisorientierte Einf\u00fchrung in die Allgemeine Betriebswirtschaftslehre \u2013 Mit Beispielen und Fallstudien|publisher=Springer Verlag|isbn=978-3-658-07106-6|edition=3rd|location=Wiesbaden|page=225|language=de|author=Joachim Paul}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is overseen by the district government of Detmold and engages in tax-privileged activities exclusively and directly in accordance with the relevant tax regulations.<ref name=\"Satzung\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Corporate/Organisation/Satzung_der_Bertelsmann_Stiftung_2019.pdf|title=Satzung der Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|format=PDF|access-date={{date|2020-04-01|mdy}}|date={{date|2019-04-05|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n=== Boards ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung's managerial and representative bodies report to the [[executive Board]], which, according to the foundation\u2019s bylaws, consists of at least three members who are appointed and removed by the board of trustees. The executive board develops the Bertelsmann Stiftung's organizational strategy, coordinates it with the [[board of trustees]] and oversees its implementation. Members of the executive board who are also members of the executive board of ''Bertelsmann Management SE'' can only represent the foundation in collaboration with a second board member who does not belong to the executive board of ''Bertelsmann Management SE'', which is the Bertelsmann Group\u2019s management unit.<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> At present, the Bertelsmann Stiftung executive board consists of Aart De Geus (chairman),<ref>{{cite news|title=St\u00fchler\u00fccken bei Bertelsmann|date={{date|2012-04-28|mdy}}|language=de|author=Oliver Horst|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> Liz Mohn (vice-chairwoman), J\u00f6rg Dr\u00e4ger and [[Brigitte Mohn]].<ref name=\"Organisation\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/ueber-uns/wer-wir-sind/organisation/|title=Organisation|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2018-01-12|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nThe executive board is advised and supervised by the Bertelsmann Stiftung board of trustees. This is involved in all decisions of fundamental importance. Its tasks also include approving the annual financial statements, overseeing the foundation's business management and formally accepting and approving the executive board's statement of activities. According to the bylaws, the board of trustees has at least six and a maximum of 14 members. These include the chairman or another member of the [[supervisory board]] of the Bertelsmann Group; a successor to Bertelsmann Stiftung founder Reinhard Mohn; Liz Mohn; and three to 11 other persons.<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> The Bertelsmann Stiftung board of trustees currently includes Werner J. Bauer (chairman), Liz Mohn (vice-chairwoman), Wolf Bauer, Carsten Coesfeld,<ref>{{cite news|language=de|title=Achten Sie auf \u2026 Carsten Coesfeld|newspaper=Manager Magazin|number=8|year=2008|url=http://heft.manager-magazin.de/MM/2018/8/158462564/index.html|access-date={{date|2018-07-20|mdy}}}}</ref> [[Thomas Buberl]], Ulrike Detmers,<ref>{{cite news |language=de |title=Neues Mitglied in namhaftem Kreis |newspaper=G\u00fctersloher Zeitung |date={{date|2017-10-25|mdy}} |page=10}}</ref> Ralph Heck, Wolfgang A. Herrmann, Christoph Mohn, Carolina M\u00fcller-M\u00f6hl, [[Viviane Reding]], [[Philipp R\u00f6sler]],<ref>{{cite news |language=de |title=Philipp R\u00f6sler im Kuratorium |newspaper=Die Glocke |date={{date|2017-12-22|mdy}} |page=17}}</ref> and J\u00fcrgen Stark.<ref name=\"Organisation\" />\n\n=== Funding ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung is funded primarily by dividends from the Bertelsmann Group. In the 2019 [[Fiscal year|financial year]], funding from this source totaled \u20ac130.0 million, or 96% of the revenues.<ref name=\"Finanzen\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Publikationen/Infomaterialien/IN_Jahresbericht_2019_DE_2_2020_03_09.pdf|language=de|format=PDF|title=Jahresbericht 2019|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|access-date={{date|2020-04-01|mdy}}|pages=8\u201311}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung holds its shares in the Bertelsmann Group indirectly through ''Johannes Mohn GmbH'', in which it holds a majority interest. The foundation's Bertelsmann Group shares are solely capital shares; voting rights are held by the ''Bertelsmann Verwaltungsgesellschaft mbH''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reinhard Mohn verzichtet auf seine Stimmrechte|date={{date|1999-07-02|mdy}}|page=13|language=de|newspaper=B\u00f6rsen-Zeitung}}</ref> Additional funding comes from partnerships with other non-profit organizations, income from the foundation's assets and donations. The Bertelsmann Stiftung sets aside reserves&nbsp;as required by the relevant tax regulations in order to pursue its activities independently of current income.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hilfe f\u00fcr die klammen Kommunen: 40 Millionen Euro in die R\u00fccklage|date={{date|2015-05-06|mdy}}|page=25|language=de|author=Lothar Schmalen|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> In the 2019 financial year, these reserves amounted to \u20ac534 million.<ref name=\"Finanzen\" />\n\nSince its establishment, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has invested a total of \u20ac1.5 billion in charitable work. In the 2019 financial year, expenditures amounted to around \u20ac90.5 million. The majority (\u20ac51.9 million) was spent on programs and special projects; \u20ac11.7 million were spent on administrative activities, \u20ac8.6 million on communication and \u20ac4.7 million on project-related services. In addition, the Bertelsmann Stiftung made grants to affiliated [[Nonprofit organization|non-profit organizations]] in the amount of \u20ac13.6 million.<ref name=\"Finanzen\" />\n\n=== Locations ===\n[[File:Postkarte_Nebenstelle_Reichsbank_Moltkestra\u00dfe_G\u00fctersloh.jpg|thumb|Reichsbank branch in G\u00fctersloh (historical postcard motif)]]\n\nThe first offices of the Bertelsmann Stiftung were located in a residential building on G\u00fctersloh's Carl-Miele-Stra\u00dfe. In 1980, offices were rented from the Bertelsmann Group instead. In 1986, the Bertelsmann Stiftung moved to a historic building on Moltkestra\u00dfe, which had been erected by a subsidiary of the [[Reichsbank]] in 1893 and was owned by the central bank of the state of North Rhine-Westphalia until 1985.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> In 1989, the architecture firm [[Gerkan, Marg and Partners]] won a competition to design the new headquarters of the Bertelsmann Stiftung opposite the headquarters of the Bertelsmann Group.<ref name=\"Gerkan, Mang und Partner\" /> The building was completed in 1990 and expanded several times over the following years.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> In addition to the head office in G\u00fctersloh, the Bertelsmann Group has an office in the Kommandantenhaus in Berlin, which is also used by the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kommandantur wird nachgebaut|date={{date|2000-11-21|mdy}}|page=23|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Das Kommandantenhaus kehrt zur\u00fcck|date={{date|1999-09-29|mdy}}|page=14|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Terrakotta-Adler im Anflug auf das Kommandantenhaus|date={{date|2003-06-13|mdy}}|page=35|language=de|author=Konrad Jahr|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref> Furthermore, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has an office in the [[Brussels and the European Union#European Quarter|European Quarter]] in [[City of Brussels|Brussels]].<ref>{{cite web|language=de|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Publikationen/Infomaterialien/IN_Jahresbericht_2017_DE_2018-03-08.pdf|title=Standorte|website=Jahresbericht 2018|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|page=11|access-date={{date|2018-03-15|mdy}}|format=PDF}}</ref>\n\nIn the mid-1990s, the Fundaci\u00f3n Bertelsmann, an independent subsidiary foundation, was established in [[Barcelona]], the capital of Catalonia. The aim was to promote reading and media literacy in Spain.<ref>{{cite book|title=Schl\u00fcsselmomente: Erfahrungen eines engagierten Lebens|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2011|isbn=978-3-641-07123-3|location=M\u00fcnchen|page=97|language=de|author=Liz Mohn}}</ref> Today, the Fundaci\u00f3n Bertelsmann focuses on vocational training and career guidance for young people in Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/index.php?id=4056|title=Fundaci\u00f3n Bertelsmann|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nSince 2008, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has also been represented in US-capital [[Washington, D.C.|Washington, D.C]], by a second independent foundation, the Bertelsmann Foundation North America, which addresses challenges relating to transatlantic partnerships.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Stiftung zieht\u2019s nach Washington|date={{date|2008-04-16|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Schl\u00fcsselmomente: Erfahrungen eines engagierten Lebens|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2011|isbn=978-3-641-07123-3|location=M\u00fcnchen|page=30|language=de|author=Liz Mohn}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/index.php?id=4057|title=Bertelsmann Foundation North America|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-12|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n== Activities ==\nAccording to its bylaws, the purpose of the Bertelsmann Stiftung is to \"promote science and research, religion, public health, youth and elderly welfare, art and culture, public and professional education, social welfare, an international perspective, democracy and social engagement.\"<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is a private operating foundation and does not make grants.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fingerzeige aus der Denkfabrik|date={{date|2014-04-30|mdy}}|page=12|language=de|author=Thorsten G\u00f6decker|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sch\u00fcssel: Kurator in deutscher Stiftung|date={{date|2007-04-20|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=Die Presse}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung \u2013 Info|date={{date|2010-11-03|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Rheinische Post}}</ref> It invests funds in projects that it conceives, initiates and implements itself.<ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|page=295|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2007/46/Bertelsmann|title=Wo geht es hier zur Zukunft?|date={{date|2007-11-11|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Zeit|author=G\u00f6tz Hamann}}</ref> For example, the Bertelsmann Stiftung produces studies and rankings,<ref>{{cite news|title=Eine Studie der Bertelsmann-Stiftung: Lesen im multimedialen Zeitalter|date={{date|1994-03-04|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung|author=Anna Katharina Ulrich}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Wirtschaftsstandort Deutschland unter Beschuss|date={{date|2004-10-08|mdy}}|page=28|language=de|newspaper=Wiener Zeitung}}</ref> conducts model projects,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bessere Bildungschancen f\u00fcr sozial Schwache|date={{date|2010-02-24|mdy}}|page=30|language=de|newspaper=Heilbronner Stimme}}</ref> shares knowledge and expertise,<ref>{{cite news|title=Orientierung im Dschungel der Medizin|date={{date|2008-06-05|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Stern|author=Thomas Osterkorn}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Von Verkaufsrhetorik bis Yoga: Volkshochschule pr\u00e4sentiert neues Programm; Zusammenarbeit mit Bertelsmann-Stiftung|date={{date|2000-09-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=S\u00fcdkurier}}</ref> organizes congresses and awards prizes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Symposium der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2000-09-07|mdy}}|page=1|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Ein Preis f\u00fcr die Schule der Zukunft|date={{date|2000-05-29|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Passauer Neue Presse}}</ref> Key fields are education, democracy, social affairs, health, the economy and culture.<ref>{{cite news|title=De Geus wird Chef der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2012-08-07|mdy}}|page=46|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung does not engage in partisan politics.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung setzt sich f\u00fcr das Gemeinwohl ein|date={{date|2008-01-19|mdy}}|edition=Bad Homburg|page=7|language=de|newspaper=Taunus-Zeitung}}</ref> It works regionally, nationally and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/unsere-projekte/|title=Unsere Projekte|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Gemeinwohl und Eigeninteresse: Das globale Engagement der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2007-03-30|mdy}}|page=68|language=de|author=Rudolph Bauer|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref>\n\n=== Education ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung examines at regular intervals how much the [[States of Germany|Germany's states]] are investing in early childhood education and care. One of its studies confirmed, for instance, that children's developmental opportunities depend heavily on their background.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2008/24/C-Interview-Stein/komplettansicht|title=Der Kita-Report|date={{date|2008-06-05|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|author=Jeannette Otto|newspaper=Die Zeit}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.taz.de/!5314782/|title=Zweiter Platz f\u00fcr Bremen|date={{date|2016-06-29|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung|author=J\u00f6rdis Fr\u00fcchtenicht}}</ref> In the field of school education, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been devoting itself in recent years to [[all-day school]]s in particular and has called for their expansion.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mehr Ganztagsschulen|date={{date|2013-08-05|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Osnabr\u00fccker Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Gutes Zeugnis f\u00fcr Ganztagsschulen|date={{date|2016-09-20|mdy}}|page=11|language=de|newspaper=Berliner Morgenpost}}</ref> Digital learning is also an important issue,<ref>{{cite news|title=Digitales Lernen scheitert oft am WLAN|date={{date|2016-08-26|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> as it is seen as a solution to various structural problems in the area of education.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lernen lernen und Kenner kennen|date={{date|2015-10-12|mdy}}|pages=92\u201393|language=de|newspaper=Profil|author=Michaela Ernst}}</ref> In addition, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has also been involved for years in vocational education and training.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung mit Angebot zur beruflichen Weiterbildung|date={{date|1994-06-23|mdy}}|page=83|language=de|author=Christian G\u00fcntlisberger|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref>\n\nIn the 1990s, the Bertelsmann Stiftung's activities in the area of higher education&nbsp;received particularly widespread public attention,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung will die Bildungspolitik pr\u00e4gen|date={{date|1998-12-10|mdy}}|page=6|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> for example the establishment of the ''Centre for Higher Education (CHE)'' in 1994 by the Bertelsmann Stiftung and the [[German Rectors' Conference]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Verbraucherzentrale f\u00fcr die Unis: Das Centrum f\u00fcr Hochschulentwicklung in G\u00fctersloh nimmt die Arbeit auf|date={{date|1994-03-03|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel|author=Thomas Veser}}</ref> This institution sees itself as a \"workshop\" for developing reforms for Germany\u2019s&nbsp;higher education institutions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2000/07/200007.artikel_44_.xml|title=Ein Grund zum Feiern|date={{date|2000-02-10|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Zeit|author=Sabine Etzold}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Der Meister-Ranker|date={{date|2005-05-22|mdy}}|page=78|language=de|newspaper=NZZ am Sonntag}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung holds 90% of the shares in ''CHE Gemeinn\u00fctziges Centrum f\u00fcr Hochschulentwicklung GmbH''.<ref name=\"Unternehmensregister\">{{cite web|url=https://www.unternehmensregister.de/|title=Unternehmensregister|publisher=Bundesanzeiger Verlag|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n=== Democracy ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung is committed on both the national and the international level to strengthening democracy through the promotion of citizen participation in political decision-making and planning processes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mehr direkte Demokratie|date={{date|2014-09-05|mdy}}|page=22|language=de|author=Simone Lutz|newspaper=Badische Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mehr B\u00fcrgerbeteiligung st\u00e4rkt die Demokratie|date={{date|2014-09-06|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Aachener Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung w\u00fcrdigt B\u00fcrgerbeteiligung in Brasilien|date={{date|2011-06-16|mdy}}|language=de|author=dapd Nachrichtenagentur}}</ref> With regard to cooperation between Germany's federal government, state and local institutions, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been calling for several years for a revision of the system used to redistribute income among the country's states.<ref>{{cite news|title=Entmachtung der Bundesl\u00e4nder|date={{date|2012-09-28|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|author=Jens Tartler|newspaper=Financial Times Deutschland}}</ref> The focus of the foundation's work in the field of democracy, however, is [[Europe]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Schwerpunkt Europa: Bertelsmann Stiftung reagiert auf kritische Umfrageergebnisse|date={{date|2012-09-17|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Europa im Fokus der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2016-05-19|mdy}}|page=1|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> For years, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has advocated accelerating the [[European Union|EU]]'s decision-making processes and promoting [[European integration]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung pl\u00e4diert f\u00fcr eine Beschleunigung der Entscheidungsprozesse \u2013 Europa braucht eine Stimme und ein Gesicht \u2013 Br\u00fcsseler Kommission sollte verkleinert und gest\u00e4rkt werden|date={{date|2006-06-19|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Agra-Europe}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Europa weiterbauen: Bertelsmann Stiftung stellt Jahresplanung vor|date={{date|2013-05-01|mdy}}|language=de|author=Bernhard Hertlein|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> Internationally, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is researching existing governance structures and developing proposals to change them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thielen trifft Ban Ki-Moon: Internationale Konferenz der Bertelsmann Stiftung in Berlin|date={{date|2008-07-18|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung kooperiert mit Institut f\u00fcr Weltwirtschaft|date={{date|2011-04-19|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> One example is the concept of a non-profit rating agency.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ideen f\u00fcr neue Rating-Agentur|date={{date|2012-04-18|mdy}}|page=33|language=de|author=Matthias Benz|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref>\n\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung also helped fund the ''Center for Applied Policy Research (CAP)'' in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.taz.de/!220824/|title=Abgang des Vorzeige-Bertelsmanns|date={{date|2007-10-31|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung|author=Max H\u00e4gler}}</ref> The center was founded by Werner Weidenfeld, who was also a member of the Bertelsmann Stiftung executive board until 2007.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ende einer wunderbaren Freundschaft|date={{date|2007-11-01|mdy}}|page=27|language=de|author=Peter Dittmar|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|pages=320\u2013326|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref> Both institutions cooperated on a number of issues, including European integration.<ref>{{cite news|title=Europa, die komplizierte Grossbaustelle|date={{date|1999-09-27|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung|author=Martin Breitenstein}}</ref> The center is affiliated with the Geschwister Scholl Institute of Political Science at [[Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cap-lmu.de/cap/|title=Strategien f\u00fcr das 21. Jahrhundert|publisher=Centrum f\u00fcr angewandte Politikforschung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n=== Society ===\nOne major focus of the work done by the Bertelsmann Stiftung is demographic change in Germany, a subject on which it has published several studies.<ref>{{cite news|title=Studie: Hamburg f\u00fcr die Zukunft gut ger\u00fcstet|date={{date|2007-02-12|mdy}}|page=31|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Osten leidet besonders|date={{date|2011-03-24|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> It also promotes volunteer work and other activities that increase social cohesion,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/themen/gesellschaft-entwickeln/engagement-und-zusammenhalt/|title=Engagement und Zusammenhalt|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> in part by awarding of the \"Mein gutes Beispiel\" (My Best Practice) prize.<ref>{{cite news|title=Preis f\u00fcr Regionalmarketing|date={{date|2013-02-28|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Passauer Neue Presse}}</ref> Social justice and intergenerational equity are also important concerns,<ref>{{cite news|title=Soziale Gerechtigkeit als Zahl|date={{date|2011-01-04|mdy}}|page=24|language=de|author=Beat Gygi|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref> and one of the reasons the foundation addresses these subjects is to narrow the gap between rich and poor.<ref>{{cite news|title=Viel Nachholbedarf bei der sozialen Gerechtigkeit|date={{date|2011-01-06|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|author=Alexander Jungkunz|newspaper=N\u00fcrnberger Nachrichten}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Foundation wants to promote social integration and diversity. It advocates for creating a \"comprehensive and long-term migration architecture\" for Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fr-online.de/meinung/gastbeitrag-einwanderung-schluss-mit--einwanderung-als-ausnahme-,1472602,25000202.html|title=Schluss mit Einwanderung als Ausnahme|date={{date|2013-11-11|mdy}}|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=J\u00f6rg Dr\u00e4ger}}</ref> Other projects address young people and families. For example, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is critical of the increase in [[child poverty]] in Germany and the way the country's pension system disadvantages families.<ref>{{cite news|title=Studie: Rentenversicherung benachteiligt Familien|date={{date|2014-01-18|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Osnabr\u00fccker Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/2016-09/kinderarmut-deutschland-hartz-iv|title=Kinderarmut nimmt in Deutschland zu|date={{date|2016-09-12|mdy}}|website=Zeit Online|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Andreas Gebert}}</ref>\n\n=== Health ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung regularly analyzed health care in Germany for what it calls its \"Gesundheitsmonitor\" (Health-Care Monitor).<ref>{{cite news|title=Zuzahlungen \u00fcberfordern Versicherte|date={{date|2006-04-25|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Th\u00fcringer Allgemeine}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung legt Gesundheitsmonitor vor \u2013 Krankenversicherte wollen Preisbindung bei Medizin|date={{date|2010-03-12|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> Moreover, it has launched several projects in the last few years that promote informed decision-making among the public in the area of [[health care]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/themen/gesundheit-aktivieren/|title=Gesundheit aktivieren|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012154702/http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/themen/gesundheit-aktivieren/|archive-date=October 12, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The projects include the Internet portal \"Wei\u00dfe Liste\" (White List) which helps users find the doctor, hospital, nursing home or nursing service that is right for them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wei\u00dfe Liste f\u00fcr Kliniken: Neue Internetplattform hilft Patienten, das f\u00fcr sie richtige und beste Krankenhaus zu finden|date={{date|2008-06-05|mdy}}|page=31|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt|author=Pia Heinemann}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Wegweiser im Pflege-Dschungel|date={{date|2013-02-01|mdy}}|language=de|author=Judith Lacroix|newspaper=Darmst\u00e4dter Echo}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Neues Vergleichsportal f\u00fcr Heime|date={{date|2016-06-27|mdy}}|page=16|language=de|newspaper=N\u00fcrnberger Nachrichten}}</ref>\n\nWith the support of the Bertelsmann Stiftung, the Center for Hospital Management (CKM) was founded in 1994 as a research institute at the [[University of M\u00fcnster]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung: Sieben Millionen DM f\u00fcr innovative Medizinprojekte|date={{date|2000-11-02|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte-Zeitung}}</ref> In addition to research on clinical IT and logistics, the center organizes training for the clinic's staff.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kurse in M\u00fcnster: Reha-Manager werden Strategen im Wettbewerb|date={{date|1998-05-04|mdy}}|page=13|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte-Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vom Praxischef zum Gesundheitsmanager|date={{date|2004-12-08|mdy}}|page=24|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte-Zeitung}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is no longer one of the shareholders of the ''CKM Centrum f\u00fcr Krankenhausmanagement GmbH.''<ref name=\"Unternehmensregister\" /> The institute has become a completely independent organization.<ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|pages=458\u2013459|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref>\n\n=== Culture ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung's oldest project in the field of culture is the competition [[Neue Stimmen]] (New Voices) international singing competition,<ref>{{cite news|title=Neue Stimmen im Wettstreit|date={{date|1991-10-31|mdy}}|page=17|language=de|newspaper=Bonner General-Anzeiger}}</ref> which was launched by Liz Mohn in 1987 and still takes place today.<ref>{{cite news|title=Musik geh\u00f6rt zu meinem Leben|date={{date|2013-03-13|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Neue Stimmen in der Stadt|date={{date|2011-10-20|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> It is one of the world's most important competitions for up-and-coming opera singers and is known as a \"showcase for new talent.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Neue Stimmen f\u00fcr die Oper|date={{date|2002-12-17|mdy}}|page=11|language=de|newspaper=Berliner Kurier}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Meisterkurse offen f\u00fcr Besucher|date={{date|2016-10-06|mdy}}|page=13|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung promotes an engagement with music in other ways as well. Model projects in this area have been carried out repeatedly since the end of the 1990s to achieve a number of objectives, including more and better [[music education]] in [[preschool]]s.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mit Musik zu besserer Leistung|date={{date|1999-08-13|mdy}}|page=28|language=de|author=Gudrun Weitzenb\u00fcrger|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Drei neue Caddys f\u00fcr Mika|date={{date|2014-09-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mit Musik lernen Kinder besser sprechen|date={{date|2016-12-13|mdy}}|page=26|language=de|author=J\u00f6rg Janssen|newspaper=Rheinische Post}}</ref> The goal is to increase social participation through singing and music.<ref>{{cite news|title=Singen: Hymne der Woche|date={{date|2001-12-23|mdy}}|page=34|language=de|newspaper=Welt am Sonntag}}</ref>\n\n=== Economy ===\nThe foundation has examined the impact of globalization on society is examined in terms of the opportunities and risks it presents.<ref>{{cite news|title=Globalisierung hilft Reichen \u2013 Deutschland geh\u00f6rt laut der Bertelsmann Stiftung zu den Gewinnern der weltweiten Verflechtung|date={{date|2014-03-25|mdy}}|page=19|language=de|newspaper=Badische Zeitung}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung advocates for developed countries to open their markets so that emerging economies can benefit more from economic developments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeit.de/wirtschaft/2016-09/weltwirtschaft-globalisierung-bertelsmann-schwellenlaender-industrielaender-handelsabkommen-thiess-petersen|title=Die Industriel\u00e4nder m\u00fcssen ihre M\u00e4rkte \u00f6ffnen|date={{date|2016-09-02|mdy}}|website=Zeit Online|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Jakob Pontius}}</ref> It has repeatedly published analyses and studies on changes in the German labor market,<ref>{{cite news|title=Der gro\u00dfe Deutschland-Check|date={{date|2002-04-04|mdy}}|page=16|language=de|author=Rainer H\u00fcbner|newspaper=Capital}}</ref> and the findings were partly incorporated into the Hartz reforms carried out during the [[Gerhard Schr\u00f6der]] government.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/unternehmen/it-medien/enthuellungsbuch-schlimme-vorwuerfe-gegen-bertelsmann-stiftung/3513246.html|title=Schlimme Vorw\u00fcrfe gegen Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2010-08-11|mdy}}|website=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Think-tanks in Germany: The Bertelsmann Foundations's Role in Labour Market Reform|year=2008|pages=437\u2013457|language=en|author=Hartwig Pautz|newspaper=Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Politikberatung|number=3/4}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is also committed to promoting sustainability and ensuring German businesses act in a socially responsible manner.<ref>{{cite news|title=L\u00e4nder-Stresstest: Deutschland bei Nachhaltigkeit nur gut|date={{date|2015-09-09|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Th\u00fcringer Allgemeine}}</ref> In collaboration with the [[Hans B\u00f6ckler|Hans B\u00f6ckler Foundation]], it carried out a study on employee participation in German companies.<ref>{{cite news|title=Miteinander statt gegeneinander zum Erfolg|date={{date|1994-09-30|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Stark in Unternehmenskultur|date={{date|2004-10-01|mdy}}|page=16|language=de|newspaper=Junge Karriere}}</ref>\n\n== Criticism ==\nIn recent years, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been the subject of public debate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmannkritik.de/|title=Bertelsmannkritik|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> In 2007, Jens Wernicke and Torsten Bultmann published an anthology, entitled \"Netzwerk der Macht \u2013 Bertelsmann\" (\"Network of Power \u2013 Bertelsmann\"),<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung kritisch im Blick|date={{date|2007-03-29|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> which takes a critical look at the structure and activities of the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nichts Neues? Da irrt Liz Mohn|date={{date|2007-05-22|mdy}}|page=3|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> The book's 30 contributors focused in particular on the foundation's non-profit status and [[Power (social and political)|political influence]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.handelsblatt.com/mediawatcher/2007/05/24/autoren-greifen-bertelsmann-stiftung-an/|title=Autoren greifen Bertelsmann Stiftung an|date={{date|2007-05-24|mdy}}|website=Medienwatcher|publisher=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter-Siebenhaar}}</ref> The anthology generated widespread public debate on the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Debatte \u00fcber Bertelsmann bef\u00f6rdert|date={{date|2007-08-03|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\nPublished in 2010, the book \"Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland \u2013 eine Stiftung macht Politik\" (\"Bertelsmann's Republic of Germany: A Foundation Sets Policy\") by author and journalist Thomas Schuler gained even greater attention.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deutschlandfunk.de/nur-im-eigenen-interesse.1310.de.html?dram:article_id=194162|title=Nur im eigenen Interesse|date={{date|2010-08-23|mdy}}|website=Deutschlandfunk|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Ralph Gerstenberg}}</ref> In it, Schuler describes how the Bertelsmann Stiftung seeks to make contact with leading politicians and to [[Political consulting|advise]] them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Schuler schreibt \u00fcber Bertelsmannrepublik|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> He criticized the Bertelsmann Stiftung as being \"undemocratic\" and lacking in transparency.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Stiftung ist undemokratisch|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bei Fragen zu Details stie\u00df ich an Grenzen|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> In his opinion, the originally good idea behind the foundation developed into a \"distorted world,\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Wahrheiten und Gemeinheiten|date={{date|2010-08-20|mdy}}|page=57|language=de|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> the basic organization of which he called into question.<ref>{{cite news|title=Politik aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2010-09-13|mdy}}|page=7|language=de|author=Harald Schumann|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref> Schuler also criticized German foundation law, which allows foundations such as the Bertelsmann Stiftung to exist at all.<ref name=\"2010-08-09\" /> Peter Rawert, an expert on foundations, noted that the Bertelsmann Stiftung is guaranteed a return on its holdings in the Bertelsmann Group that is probably lower than what could be achieved with a [[Fixed income|fixed-income]] [[investment]]. He also noted that in the United States this would have a negative impact on the foundation's non-profit tax status; moreover, he argued that the situation does not reflect the \"standard of efficiency\" normally endorsed by the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Grundg\u00fctiges aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2010-09-14|mdy}}|page=35|language=de|newspaper=Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung}}</ref>\n\n=== Commercial interests ===\nDue to its majority interest in the Bertelsmann Group, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been repeatedly accused of combining [[non-profit]] and [[profit (economics)|commercial interests]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deutschlandradiokultur.de/die-guetersloher-nebenregierung.950.de.html?dram:article_id=139101|title=Die G\u00fctersloher Nebenregierung|date={{date|2010-08-31|mdy}}|website=Deutschlandradio Kultur|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Vera Lin\u00df}}</ref> In 2009, the journalist and author Annette Jensen asserted that the Bertelsmann Stiftung's proposals [[demand generation|generate artificial demand]], particularly in terms of the purported need to [[Small government|streamline local government]], a demand which the foundation then meets, for example through the Bertelsmann subsidiary [[Arvato]]. She suggested that the [[RTL Television|RTL]] and [[VOX (German TV channel)|VOX]] television stations belonging to the Bertelsmann Group and numerous [[Gruner + Jahr]] magazines served the foundation by disseminating its messages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://publik.verdi.de/2009/ausgabe_01_02/gesellschaft/.gesellschaft/seite_9/A0|title=Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeit ist ein gutes Gesch\u00e4ft|date=2009|website=ver.di Publik|publisher=Vereinte Dienstleistungsgewerkschaft|page=9|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Annette Jensen}}</ref> The sociologist and entrepreneur Frank Adloff has argued that it is indefensible that the foundation does not need to justify the use of its funds before any parliament or oversight authority. In the United States, he noted, non-profit foundations are not permitted to hold more than a 20% stake in a company in order to avoid possible [[conflict of interest|conflicts of interest]]; in addition, they have to provide a [[public accounting]] of their expenditures.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\" />\n\n=== Political influence ===\nAnother criticism involves a lack of [[Legitimacy (political)|democratic legitimacy]]. Commenting on the foundation's \"engagement with civil society,\" Wolfgang Lieb, former state secretary in the North Rhine-Westphalia [[Ministry of Science]], has argued that this legitimacy is being increasingly diminished, and even replaced by, [[economic power]]. According to Lieb, private networks and behind-the-scenes advisors are thus turning into actual rulers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nachdenkseiten.de/?p=2144|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung und ihre Verflechtungen / Referat im Rahmen einer Vortragsreihe des Rosa-Luxemburg-Clubs Wuppertal|date={{date|2007-02-26|mdy}}|website=Nachdenkseiten|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Wolfgang Lieb}}</ref> By consulting with politicians outside of government settings, Lieb suggests, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is pursuing a \"[[privatization]] of politics,\" a situation that offers mutual benefits: [[civil servant]]s and politicians are given a protected space where they alone are provided with information free of charge and where they can engage in discussion, while the Bertelsmann Stiftung secures access to all the projects it wants to influence. Thus, no matter who is elected, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is always part of the government.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\" /> Speaking with broadcaster [[Deutschlandfunk]] in 2007, the former [[Social Democratic Party of Germany|SPD]] politician and publicist Albrecht M\u00fcller called the foundation an \"[[anti-democratic]] institution.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nachdenkseiten.de/?p=2231|title=Deutschlandfunk Zwischent\u00f6ne als Audio \u2013 Ein Experiment bei den Nachdenkseiten (Mitschnitt der Sendung)|date={{date|2007-04-03|mdy}}|website=Nachdenkseiten|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the journalist and politician Julika Sandt criticized the growing influence of the Bertelsmann Stiftung on [[German health care]], saying that initiatives developed by the foundation lead to preferential treatment for [[privatized clinic]]s and medical care centers to the detriment of self-employed physicians. According to Sandt, because Brigitte Mohn is a member of both the Bertelsmann Stiftung executive board and the supervisory board of [[Rh\u00f6n-Klinikum]], the foundation's neutrality in the health sector is questionable.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bzb-online.de/apr08/10_11.pdf|title=F\u00e4den der Macht: Die Bertelsmann-Connection und das Ende der Freiberuflichkeit|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|year=2008|pages=10\u201311|language=de|format=PDF|newspaper=Bayerisches Zahn\u00e4rzteblatt|author=Julika Sandt}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Josef Kraus, president of the {{ill|German Teachers' Association|de|Deutscher Lehrerverband}}, spoke critically about the influence of the Bertelsmann Stiftung on [[education policy]]. He described its studies as \"[[unscientific]]\" and as \"[[scare tactics]].\" Its activities almost always involved turning some alleged administrative failure into a scandal, Kraus said. He called on politicians to stop allowing themselves to be influenced by the Bertelsmann Stiftung and to take criticism of the foundation seriously.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lehrerverband.de/aktuell_Dossier_Bertelsmannstudien_Dez_12.html|title=\u00dcber den Wert von Bertelsmann-Studien|date=December 2012|publisher=Deutscher Lehrerverband|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Josef Kraus|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702113018/http://www.lehrerverband.de/aktuell_Dossier_Bertelsmannstudien_Dez_12.html|archive-date=July 2, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe non-profit organization Lobbycontrol sees the Bertelsmann Stiftung as a business-oriented initiative, similar to the \"[[Initiative Neue Soziale Marktwirtschaft]]\" (Initiative for a New Social Market Economy) or the \"[[Stiftung Marktwirtschaft]]\" (Free Market Foundation).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lobbypedia.de/wiki/Bertelsmann_Stiftung|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2016-12-20|mdy}}|website=Lobbycontrol|language=de|access-date={{date|2017-03-06|mdy}}}}</ref> Lobbycontrol criticizes, for example, the \"Standortcheck\" (Business Location Check), which it says amounts to a canonical neoliberal reform.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.socialtimes.de/nachricht.php?nachricht_id=7704&newsrubrik_id=6|title=B\u00fcrgerrechtler kritisieren Bertelsmann Stiftung|website=Social Times|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928063204/http://www.socialtimes.de/nachricht.php?nachricht_id=7704&newsrubrik_id=6|archive-date={{date|2007-09-28|mdy}}|url-status = dead|access-date={{date|2017-03-06|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung has repeatedly refuted criticism asserting a lack of democratic legitimacy and unpermitted political influence. For example, Gunter Thielen, former chairman and CEO of the Bertelsmann Stiftung, made it clear that the foundation was not a \"secret government,\" that the formation of public opinion and policy is not a \"top-down process,\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/unternehmen/it-medien/gunter-thielen-wir-sind-keine-heimliche-regierung/3572788.html|title=Wir sind keine heimliche Regierung|date={{date|2010-10-25|mdy}}|website=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar}}</ref> and that it was unimaginable that a foundation or a company could use its own ideas to influence or control a country like the Federal Republic of Germany.<ref name=\"2010-08-09\">{{cite web|url=http://www.taz.de/!5137692/|title=Politischer Einfluss illusorisch|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|website=Die Tageszeitung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Steffen Grimberg}}</ref>\n\n=== Political neutrality ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung describes itself as politically non-partisan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Publikationen/Infomaterialien/IN_BSt_Auf_einenBlick_D_2015.pdf|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung auf einen Blick|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|format=PDF|access-date={{date|2017-01-31|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.die-glocke.de/lokalnachrichten/kreisguetersloh/guetersloh/Piraten-kritisieren-Bertelsmann-Stiftung-79136bfe-bce7-4e4d-a32d-f0ff4644d2e0-ds|title=Piraten kritisieren Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2016-12-02|mdy}}|website=Die Glocke|language=de|access-date={{date|2017-01-31|mdy}}}}</ref> The practical implementation of this principle, however, has been questioned from several sides, in particular because the foundation has only established contacts with \"radical supporters of market policies\" among left-leaning parties.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\" /> In turn, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has often been characterized as a proponent of [[economic liberalism]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Abkehr von der Globalisierung|date={{date|2016-09-01|mdy}}|page=1|language=de|author=Wolfgang B\u00f6hm|newspaper=Die Presse}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=B\u00fcrgergesellschaft als Projekt: Eine Bestandsaufnahme zu Entwicklung und F\u00f6rderung zivilgesellschaftlicher Potenziale in Deutschland|publisher=Verlag f\u00fcr Sozialwissenschaften|year=2009|isbn=978-3-531-16266-9|editor=Ansgar Klein |editor2=Ralf Kleinfeld |editor3=Frank Nullmeier |editor4=Dieter Rucht |editor5=Heike Walk |editor6=Ulrich Willems |editor7=Annette Zimmer |display-editors=3|location=Wiesbaden|page=288|language=de|newspaper=B\u00fcrgergesellschaft und Demokratie}}</ref> but this is also controversial;<ref>{{cite book|title=Politikberatung und die Herstellung von Entscheidungssicherheit im politischen System|publisher=Verlag f\u00fcr Sozialwissenschaften|year=2008|isbn=978-3-531-16048-1|location=Wiesbaden|page=236|language=de|author=Isabel Kusche}}</ref> some critics have also labeled the Bertelsmann Stiftung [[Neoliberalism|neoliberal]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Wo bleiben die Visionen?|date={{date|2009-11-12|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|author=G\u00fcnter Bihn|newspaper=Frankfurter Rundschau}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Supermarkt Europa: Vom Ausverkauf unserer Demokratie|publisher=Czernin Verlag|year=2014|isbn=978-3-7076-0521-1|location=Wien|page=15|language=de|author=Robert Misik, Michel Reimon}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bonzen, Bildung, Bertelsmann \u2013 Die Bertelsmann Stiftung als Denkfabrik des Neoliberalismus|date={{date|2005-11-18|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Analyse und Kritik|number=500}}</ref>\n\n=== Non-profit status ===\nIn 2006, the author and journalist Harald Schumann discussed the non-profit status of the Bertelsmann Stiftung in the [[Der Tagesspiegel|Tagesspiegel]] newspaper. According to Schumann, the \"[[deep state|shadow government]] in G\u00fctersloh\" runs on de facto on public money, because Reinhard Mohn saved an over \u20ac2 billion euros in [[inheritance tax|inheritance]] and [[gift tax]]es when he transferred three-quarters of the Bertelsmann Group capital shares to the foundation. Moreover, he asserts, the annual dividend payment to the foundation is tax-free and, with its annual budget of around \u20ac60 million, the foundation does not spend nearly as much as it costs the state in terms of lost revenue.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tagesspiegel.de/zeitung/macht-ohne-mandat/755580.html|title=Macht ohne Mandat|date={{date|2006-09-24|mdy}}|website=Der Tagesspiegel|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Harald Schumann}}</ref> Arno Kl\u00f6nne, a sociologist and political scientist, has argued that the Bertelsmann Stiftung's non-profit nature was questionable because, he maintains, it actively promotes the business of the Bertelsmann Group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.handelsblatt.com/mediawatcher/2007/06/11/ist-die-bertelsmann-stiftung-noch-gemeinnutzig/|title=Ist die Bertelsmann Stiftung noch gemeinn\u00fctzig?|date={{date|2007-06-11|mdy}}|website=Medienwatcher|publisher=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=G\u00fctersloher Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeiten|date={{date|2007-10-31|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> Ultimately, he suggests, its goal is to manage society using corporate methods and to [[Privatization|privatize]] the tasks that should be handled by the state.<ref>{{cite news|title=Im Sitzen durchs Netzwerk|date={{date|2007-06-09|mdy}}|language=de|author=Stefan Brams|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, a group of independent legal experts found that the Bertelsmann Stiftung no longer met the requirements for a non-profit organization. On the contrary, they argued, the [[tax exemption]] was unjustly being used for the purpose of carrying out a transformation of society according to the beliefs of the Bertelsmann Stiftung's founder, Reinhard Mohn, by means of private, tax-financed private policy consulting and by bypassing democratic decision making processes through public discourse in Germany's constitutional bodies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrhz.de/flyer/beitrag.php?id=13431|title=Ist die Bertelsmann Stiftung \"gemeinn\u00fctzig\" im Sinne von \u00a7\u00a7 52 ff. AO? Eine Expertise unabh\u00e4ngiger Juristen.|date={{date|2009-02-04|mdy}}|website=Neue Rheinische Zeitung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung has always rejected these accusations, noting that its non-profit status has been recognized by the tax authorities and is reviewed on an ongoing basis.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeit wurde anerkannt \u2013 Bertelsmann Stiftung weist Wernickes Kritik zur\u00fcck|date={{date|2007-05-23|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\n=== Social welfare cuts ===\nIn 2007, the trade union ver.di terminated its cooperation with the Bertelsmann Stiftung. The reason was that Arvato, a division of the Bertelsmann Group, declared the privatization of public services a strategic business area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.handelsblatt.com/mediawatcher/2007/10/15/bertelsmann-kampft-mit-boykott-von-verdi/|title=Bertelsmann k\u00e4mpft mit Boykott von Verdi|date={{date|2007-10-15|mdy}}|website=Medienwatcher|publisher=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar}}</ref> A corresponding motion was passed at the union's federal congress against the wishes of its federal governing board.<ref name=\"2007-10-31\">{{cite news|title=Beziehungen auf Eis gelegt: Verdi setzt Zusammenarbeit mit Bertelsmann aus|date={{date|2007-10-31|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is the driving force behind privatizations and cuts to [[social welfare]] programs, critics claimed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die heimliche Regierung aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2007-11-02|mdy}}|language=de|author=Rudolf Stumberger|newspaper=VDI Nachrichten}}</ref> This assessment was supported by participants at \"Das Schattenkabinett aus G\u00fctersloh\" (\"The Shadow Cabinet from G\u00fctersloh\"), a conference critical of Bertelsmann.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Kritik schwillt weiter an|date={{date|2007-10-27|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische|author=Stefan Brams}}</ref> In addition to [[ver.di]], other participants included [[Association for the Taxation of Financial Transactions and for Citizens' Action|Attac]], [[Education and Science Workers' Union (Germany)|GEW]], [[IG Metall]] and the Otto Brenner Foundation.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kontrastreiches Programm: Bertelsmann-Kritiker kontra Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeit|date={{date|2007-10-30|mdy}}|language=de|author=Stefan Brams|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.taz.de/!5192664/|title=Eine Kasse f\u00fcr sich|date={{date|2007-10-29|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|page=17|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung|author=Daniel Bouhs}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung rejected the criticism from ver.di in particular as a \"misunderstanding,\"<ref name=\"2007-10-31\" /> saying that both sides were not that far apart in their views on social problems.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stiftung wirbt um Verdis Vertrauen|date={{date|2007-11-10|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite book|title=Bertelsmann: Hinter der Fassade des Medienimperiums|publisher=Eichborn Verlag|year=2004|isbn=3-8218-5551-7|location=Frankfurt am Main|language=de|author=Frank B\u00f6ckelmann, Hersch Fischler}}\n* {{cite book|title=Die Kunst des Stiftens: 20 Perspektiven auf Stiftungen in Deutschland|publisher=Edition Pro Arte|year=2005|isbn=3-9805009-6-9|location=Berlin|pages=22\u201325|language=de|author=Ulrich Br\u00f6mmling}}\n* {{cite book|title=Bertelsmann: Ein globales Medienimperium macht Politik / Expansion als Bildungsdienstleister und politische Einflussnahme \u2013 internationale Perspektive|publisher=Anders Verlag|year=2006|isbn=3-939594-01-6|location=Hamburg|language=de|editor=Thomas Bart}}\n* {{cite book|title=Agenda Bertelsmann: Ein Konzern stiftet Politik|publisher=Papyrossa Verlag|year=2007|isbn=978-3-89438-372-5|location=K\u00f6ln|language=de|author=Werner Biermann, Arno Kl\u00f6nne}}\n* {{cite book|title=Netzwerk der Macht \u2013 Bertelsmann / Der medial-politische Komplex aus G\u00fctersloh|publisher=Bund demokratischer Wissenschaftlerinnen und Wissenschaftler|year=2007|isbn=978-3-939864-02-8|editor=Jens Wernicke |editor2=Torsten Bultmann|location=Marburg|language=de}}\n* {{cite book|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung im Institutionengef\u00fcge \u2013 Medienpolitik aus Sicht des \u00f6konomischen Institutionalismus|publisher=Nomos Verlag|year=2008|isbn=978-3-8329-3982-3|location=Baden-Baden|language=de|author=Regina Hannerer, Christian Steininger}}\n* {{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-39097-0|location=Frankfurt am Main|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/home}}\n\n{{Coord|51|54|30|N|8|25|09|E|region:DE-NW_type:landmark|display=title}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bertelsmann Foundation}}\n[[Category:1977 establishments in West Germany]]\n[[Category:Advocacy groups in Germany]]\n[[Category:Bertelsmann]]\n[[Category:Foundations based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Political and economic research foundations]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks based in Europe]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Think tanks based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Think tanks established in 1977]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| logo = Bertelsmann Stiftung Logo.png\n| logo_alt = Logo of the Bertelsmann Stiftung\n| formation = {{start date and age|1977}}<ref>{{cite news|language=de|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung neu organisiert|newspaper=B\u00f6rsen-Zeitung|date={{date|2004-07-21|mdy}}|page=11}}</ref>\n| key_people = {{ublist|[[J\u00f6rg Dr\u00e4ger]]|[[Brigitte Mohn]]|[[Liz Mohn]]}}\n| name = Bertelsmann Stiftung\n| named_after = [[Carl Bertelsmann]]\n| logo_size = 200px\n| founder = [[Reinhard Mohn]]<ref>{{cite news|language=de|title=Im Auftrag des Patriarchen: Bertelsmann Stiftung erinnert an Reinhard Mohn|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische|date={{date|2010-05-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n| location = [[G\u00fctersloh]], [[Germany]]\n| revenue = [[Euro|\u20ac]]125.8 [[million]]<ref name=\"Finance\" />\n| revenue_year = 2018\n| expenses = \u20ac86.2 million<ref name=\"Finance\" />\n| expenses_year = 2018\n| endowment = \u20ac619.5 million<ref name=\"Finance\" />\n| endowment_year = 2018\n| staff = 384<ref name=\"Finance\" />\n| staff_year = 2018\n| motto = \"Inspiring people. Shaping the future. Participating in a globalized world.\"<ref>{{cite web|language=en|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/about-us/what-motivates-us/our-mission/|title=Mission Statement: Our Core Principles|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|access-date={{date|2017-05-31|mdy}}}}</ref>\n| website = {{URL|https://bertelsmann-stiftung.de}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Bertelsmann_Stiftung_2007-01.jpg|thumb|Headquarters of the Bertelsmann Stiftung in G\u00fctersloh (2007)]]\n\nThe '''Bertelsmann Stiftung''' is an independent [[Foundation (nonprofit)|foundation]] under private law, based in [[G\u00fctersloh]], Germany. It was founded in 1977 by [[Reinhard Mohn]] as the result of social, corporate and fiscal considerations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/unternehmen/bertelsmann-patriarch-mohn-tod-eines-wirtschaftsweisen-a-653111.html|title=Tod eines Wirtschaftsweisen|date={{date|2009-10-04|mdy}}|website=Spiegel Online|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/ueber-uns/was-uns-bewegt/motive-des-stifters/|title=Von der Welt lernen: Warum Reinhard Mohn die Bertelsmann Stiftung gr\u00fcndete|website=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2015-11-24|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.taz.de/!5137745/|title=Die Methode Bertelsmann: Eine Stiftung regiert das Land|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|website=Die Tageszeitung|language=de|access-date={{date|2015-10-01|mdy}}|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Erfolgsfaktor Unternehmenskultur: Mit kulturbewusstem Management Unternehmensziele erreichen und Identifikation schaffen|publisher=Springer Verlag|year=2004|isbn=978-3-322-82623-7|location=Wiesbaden|page=275|language=de|author=Sonja A. Sackmann}}</ref> As the Bertelsmann Stiftung itself has put it, the foundation promotes \"reform processes\" and \"the principles of entrepreneurial activity\" to build a \"future-oriented society.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.freitag.de/autoren/der-freitag/die-tonangeber|title=Die Tonangeber|date={{date|2006-06-16|mdy}}|website=Der Freitag|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nSince 1993, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has held the majority of capital shares in the [[Bertelsmann|Bertelsmann Group]].<ref name=\"1993-10-14\"/> It holds 80.9% together with the Reinhard Mohn Stiftung and the BVG Stiftung but has no voting rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann.de/unternehmen/aktionaere/|title=Aktion\u00e4rsstruktur|publisher=Bertelsmann|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-12|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Reinhard_Mohn_Portrait_2008.jpg|thumb|Reinhard Mohn (2008)]]\n\n=== Establishment of the foundation ===\nAt the end of the 1970s, there were discussions concerning who would follow Reinhard Mohn as chairman of Bertelsmann.<ref>{{cite book|title=175 Jahre Bertelsmann: Eine Zukunftsgeschichte|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-570-10175-9|location=M\u00fcnchen|pages=44\u201345|language=de}}</ref> Against this background and because he believed that the state must be able to count on its citizens' willingness to assume responsibility and take the initiative, Mohn founded the Bertelsmann Stiftung on February 8, 1977.<ref name=\"Chronicle\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/about-us/who-we-are/chronicle/|title=Chronicle|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=en|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> It was officially approved by the authorities on March 14, 1977.<ref>{{cite book|title=Die Mohns \u2013 Vom Provinzbuchh\u00e4ndler zum Weltkonzern / Die Familie hinter Bertelsmann|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2004|isbn=978-3-593-41565-9|location=Frankfurt am Main|page=291|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung was initially endowed with 100,000 [[Deutsche Mark]]s in capital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geschichte.nrw.de/artikel.php?artikel%5Bid%5D=866|title=Wettbewerb und b\u00fcrgerschaftliches Engagement|publisher=Landeszentrale f\u00fcr politische Bildung Nordrhein-Westfalen|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303201603/http://www.geschichte.nrw.de/artikel.php?artikel%5Bid%5D=866|archive-date=March 3, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Die Stadtbibliothek G\u00fctersloh GmbH: Kooperationsversuch zwischen Medienunternehmen und Kommune|publisher=Harrassowitz Verlag|year=1983|isbn=3-447-02370-8|location=Wiesbaden|page=48|language=de}}</ref> About two years later it began its work.\n\n=== Building the foundation's work ===\nIn 1979, Hans-Dieter Weger was appointed the first managing director. He developed the concept of an operational foundation that develops and oversees its own projects.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ein Anstifter des Guten|date={{date|2004-09-16|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> One of the Bertelsmann Stiftung's first activities was the [[Baseline Study|baseline study]] \"Kommunikationsverhalten und Buch\" (Communication Behavior and the Book), which was prepared in cooperation with [[Infratest dimap|Infratest]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kommunikationsverhalten und Buch: Endbericht|publisher=Infratest|year=1978|location=M\u00fcnchen|language=de|editor=Bodo Franzmann}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung and the Bertelsmann Group also provided support for&nbsp;the construction of the G\u00fctersloh municipal&nbsp;library.<ref>{{cite book|title=Die Stadtbibliothek G\u00fctersloh GmbH: Kooperationsversuch zwischen Medienunternehmen und Kommune|publisher=Harrassowitz Verlag|year=1983|isbn=3-447-02370-8|location=Wiesbaden|page=50|language=de}}</ref>\n\nIn 1982, the Bertelsmann Stiftung presented its first public report of its activities. In the report's foreword, [[Karl Carstens]], [[President of Germany|president of the Federal Republic of Germany]], praised the \"achievement of foundations in the public sphere.\"<ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|page=49|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref> In the meantime, the Bertelsmann Stiftung had come to play a central role in Reinhard Mohn's sociopolitical activities.<ref>{{cite news|title=Personalien|date={{date|1986-06-27|mdy}}|page=24|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> Mohn functioned as the foundation's sole executive and was supported by a newly created advisory board from 1983 onwards. In addition to Reinhard Mohn and Hans-Dieter Weger, the board's members were&nbsp;[[Kurt Biedenkopf]], [[Gerd Bucerius]], Friedhelm Farthmann and Eberhard Witte.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> In 1985, a publishing house was founded as part of the foundation in order to handle the growing number of publications. Verlag Bertelsmann Stiftung still exists today.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adb-online.de/|title=Profilansicht: Verlag Bertelsmann Stiftung|website=Adressbuch f\u00fcr den deutschsprachigen Buchhandel|publisher=Marketing- und Verlagsservice des Buchhandels|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nIn 1988, the Bertelsmann Stiftung awarded the Carl Bertelsmann Prize (now known as the Reinhard Mohn Prize) for the first time. The recipients were employer organizations and trade unions in the construction, chemistry and metalworking industries.<ref>{{cite news|title=Carl-Bertelsmann-Preis|date={{date|1988-04-18|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> Today, the award continues to honor internationally renowned figures&nbsp;who have developed pioneering solutions to social and political challenges.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.n-tv.de/politik/Schwab-erhaelt-Reinhard-Mohn-Preis-article17960896.html|title=Weitblick und Geschick: Schwab erh\u00e4lt Reinhard-Mohn-Preis|date={{date|2016-06-16|mdy}}|website=n-tv|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-12|mdy}}}}</ref> In addition to working in Germany, the Bertelsmann Stiftung initiated several international projects in the 1980s,<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> such as the \"Kulturraum Europa\" (European Culture Space).<ref>{{cite news|title=Einf\u00fchrung und Chronologie des Projekts Kulturraum Europa|year=2011|location=G\u00fctersloh|language=de|author=Kai Franke|newspaper=Chronik der Bertelsmann Stiftung}}</ref> Further examples include a program at the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] and the construction of the Biblioteca Can Torr\u00f3 in [[Alc\u00fadia]] on the island of Majorca.<ref>{{cite book|title=Schl\u00fcsselmomente: Erfahrungen eines engagierten Lebens|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2011|isbn=978-3-641-07123-3|location=M\u00fcnchen|page=20|language=de|author=Liz Mohn}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Alcudia macht Reinhard Mohn zum Ehrenb\u00fcrger|date={{date|2005-09-14|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gorbatschow_in_G\u00fctersloh_1992.jpg|thumb|Mikhail Gorbachev, Reinhard Mohn and Liz Mohn in the foyer of the Bertelsmann Stiftung (1992)]]\nKurt Biedenkopf was elected as the first chairman of the advisory board in 1987,<ref>{{cite news|title=Personalien|date={{date|1987-09-11|mdy}}|page=22|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> and Reinhard Mohn himself took over this position in 1990.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> Horst Teltschik then joined the foundation, a development that received a great deal of media attention. The former foreign policy adviser to [[Helmut Kohl]] became managing director of the Bertelsmann Stiftung in early 1991 and began focusing on the foundation's internationalization.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kohls Kopf bei Bertelsmann|date={{date|1990-12-06|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Teltschik will Profil der Bertelsmann Stiftung sch\u00e4rfen|date={{date|1991-02-06|mdy}}|page=9|language=de|newspaper=Bonner General-Anzeiger}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung: Teltschik setzt auf Expertenseminare und Projektf\u00f6rderung. Arbeit soll auf neue L\u00e4nder ausgedehnt und Aktuelles schneller umgesetzt werden|date={{date|1991-02-06|mdy}}|page=7|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> At the end of the 1980s, the Bertelsmann Stiftung offices were built&nbsp;opposite the Bertelsmann corporate&nbsp;headquarters.<ref name=\"Gerkan, Mang und Partner\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gmp-architekten.de/projekte/carl-bertelsmann-stiftung.html|title=Projekte|publisher=Gerkan, Marg und Partner|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/about-us/who-we-are/offices/|title=Offices|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=en|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] was a guest during his first trip to Germany after the demise&nbsp;of the [[Soviet Union]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-13855374.html|title=Deutlich darunter|date={{date|1992-03-09|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Der Spiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Niemand wird f\u00fcr uns die Probleme l\u00f6sen k\u00f6nnen|date={{date|1992-03-11|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref>\n\n=== Transferring the majority interest ===\nIn addition to Reinhard Mohn, Ulrich Saxer and Werner Weidenfeld were appointed to the Bertelsmann Stiftung [[executive board]] in 1993. New management was also hired.<ref name=\"1993-05-28\">{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung: Mohn k\u00fcndigt deutliche Etataufstockung f\u00fcr 1993/94 an; Forschungsprogramm soll Reform der sozialen Marktwirtschaft ausloten|date={{date|1993-05-28|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> In the same year, Reinhard Mohn transferred the majority of the capital shares in the&nbsp;Bertelsmann Group to the foundation, a move intended to ensure continuity at the company.<ref>{{cite book|title=175 Jahre Bertelsmann: Eine Zukunftsgeschichte|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-570-10175-9|location=M\u00fcnchen|pages=274\u2013276|language=de}}</ref> The transaction increased the foundation's stake in the company from 21.3% to 68.8%,<ref name=\"1993-10-14\" /><ref name=\"1993-05-28\" /> being the largest [[shareholder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.n-tv.de/wirtschaft/Bertelsmann-bewahrt-Tradition-article534278.html|title=Nach dem Tod von Reinhard Mohn: Bertelsmann bewahrt Tradition|date={{date|2009-10-05|mdy}}|website=n-tv|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> In the 1993 transfer agreement, however, shareholdings and voting rights were strictly separated, so that the foundation cannot exercise any significant influence on the Bertelsmann Group,<ref name=\"1993-10-14\">{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann geh\u00f6rt jetzt mehrheitlich der Stiftung|date={{date|1993-10-14|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=Deutscher Drucker}}</ref> which is still largely controlled by the Mohn family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann.de/unternehmen/aktionaere/|title=Aktion\u00e4rsstruktur|publisher=Bertelsmann|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/unternehmen/it-medien/bertelsmann-medienmonarchie-aus-guetersloh/3818956.html|title=Medienmonarchie aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2011-01-30|mdy}}|website=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> As the foundation receives dividends for its holdings in the company, the transfer of shares resulted in a significant increase in the organization's budget.<ref name=\"1993-05-28\" />\n\n=== Restructuring of governance boards ===\nIn 1998, Reinhard Mohn stepped down from his leading role at the Bertelsmann Stiftung. Mark W\u00f6ssner was first elected chairman of the executive board, and, a year later, chairman of the advisory board.<ref>{{cite news|title=Der Leitwolf verl\u00e4\u00dft das Rudel|date={{date|1998-09-24|mdy}}|page=14|language=de|author=Thomas Hoffmann|newspaper=Horizont}}</ref> After W\u00f6ssner's departure in 2000, the foundation's governance structure changed again:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tagesspiegel.de/wirtschaft/die-komplizierte-romanze-der-liz-mohn/472428.html|title=Die komplizierte Romanze der Liz Mohn|date={{date|2003-12-08|mdy}}|website=Der Tagesspiegel|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Matthew Karnitschnig}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mohn stellt die Weichen|date={{date|2000-09-29|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Allgemeine Zeitung}}</ref> the executive board was replaced by an executive committee and the advisory board was replaced by a board of trustees.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung erh\u00e4lt neue F\u00fchrungsstruktur|date={{date|2009-09-29|mdy}}|page=28|language=de|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref> As an interim step, at the end of 2000 Reinhard Mohn became chairman of both the executive committee and the board of trustees, until [[Gunter Thielen]] succeeded him in both positions in mid-2001.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mohn wird Pr\u00e4sident der Bertelsmann Stiftung / Im Juli 2002 soll Gunter Thielen das Amt \u00fcbernehmen|date={{date|2000-09-29|mdy}}|page=17|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Der Patriarch zieht sich zur\u00fcck|date={{date|2001-08-05|mdy}}|page=18|language=de|newspaper=Berliner Zeitung}}</ref> With this step, Reinhard Mohn gave up all previous management functions, remaining only a member of the board of trustees.<ref>{{cite news|title=Der Patriarch schont die Kr\u00e4fte|date={{date|2001-08-25|mdy}}|page=31|language=de|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Reinhard Mohn tritt ab|date={{date|2001-08-25|mdy}}|page=25|language=de|newspaper=Bonner General-Anzeiger}}</ref>\n\nHeribert Meffert succeeded&nbsp;Gunter Thielen in 2002 and continued to lead the Bertelsmann Stiftung until 2005.<ref>{{cite news|title=Marketing-Papst \u00fcbernimmt Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2002-08-10|mdy}}|page=27|language=de|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Meffert verl\u00e4sst Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2005-06-17|mdy}}|page=20|language=de|author=Thomas Kn\u00fcwer, Hans-Peter Siebenhaar|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> During his tenure, the executive committee became an executive board once again;<ref>{{cite news|title=Der Stifter als Bauherr|date={{date|2004-07-20|mdy}}|language=de|author=Stefan Brams|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> the goal was to strengthen corporate governance by promoting greater transparency and independence.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wir wollen keine geheimen Ministerien sein|date={{date|2005-04-29|mdy}}|language=de|author=Marc Beise, Hans-J\u00fcrgen Jakobs|newspaper=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung}}</ref> After Meffert left the foundation, it was jointly led by board chairs [[Liz Mohn]] and Johannes Meier.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/karriere/a-360818.html|title=Meffert geht fr\u00fcher|date={{date|2005-06-16|mdy}}|website=Manager Magazin|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> In 2008, Gunter Thielen returned to the Bertelsmann Stiftung as chairman of the executive board.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/karriere/a-309347.html|title=Thielen wird Stiftungsleiter|date={{date|2004-07-19|mdy}}|website=Manager Magazin|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.horizont.net/medien/nachrichten/-Gunter-Thielen-geht-zurueck-zur-Bertelsmann-Stiftung-73885|title=Gunter Thielen geht zur\u00fcck zur Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2008-01-03|mdy}}|website=Horizont|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-01|mdy}}}}</ref> Since 2012, the foundation has been led by [[Aart de Geus|Aart De Geus]], former Dutch minister of labor and social affairs.<ref>{{cite news|title=Regierungswechsel in G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2012-08-04|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Ab August Chef der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2012-05-03|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|author=David Hein|newspaper=Horizont}}</ref> Following his retirement at the end of 2019, it was announced that Ralph Heck would take over as chairman of the executive board in mid-2020.<ref>{{cite web|language=de|url=https://www.welt.de/regionales/nrw/article201310968/Neuer-Chef-fuer-Bertelsmann-Stiftung-Heck-loest-De-Geus-ab.html|title=Neuer Chef f\u00fcr Bertelsmann-Stiftung: Heck l\u00f6st De Geus ab|website=Welt Online|date={{date|2019-10-02|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2020-01-31|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n== Organization ==\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung is an independent foundation under private law, according to the laws governing foundations in the state of [[North Rhine-Westphalia]].<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> It is an unrestricted legal entity, which, internally and externally, must exclusively pursue the mission defined in its bylaws.<ref>{{cite book|title=Praxisorientierte Einf\u00fchrung in die Allgemeine Betriebswirtschaftslehre \u2013 Mit Beispielen und Fallstudien|publisher=Springer Verlag|isbn=978-3-658-07106-6|edition=3rd|location=Wiesbaden|page=225|language=de|author=Joachim Paul}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is overseen by the district government of Detmold and engages in tax-privileged activities exclusively and directly in accordance with the relevant tax regulations.<ref name=\"Satzung\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Corporate/Organisation/Satzung_BertelsmannStiftung_20140402.pdf|title=Satzung der Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|format=PDF|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404132409/http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Corporate/Organisation/Satzung_BertelsmannStiftung_20140402.pdf|archive-date=April 4, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Boards ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung's managerial and representative bodies report to the [[executive Board]], which, according to the foundation\u2019s bylaws, consists of at least three members who are appointed and removed by the board of trustees. The executive board develops the Bertelsmann Stiftung's organizational strategy, coordinates it with the [[board of trustees]] and oversees its implementation. Members of the executive board who are also members of the executive board of ''Bertelsmann Management SE'' can only represent the foundation in collaboration with a second board member who does not belong to the executive board of ''Bertelsmann Management SE'', which is the Bertelsmann Group\u2019s management unit.<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> At present, the Bertelsmann Stiftung executive board consists of Aart De Geus (chairman),<ref>{{cite news|title=St\u00fchler\u00fccken bei Bertelsmann|date={{date|2012-04-28|mdy}}|language=de|author=Oliver Horst|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> Liz Mohn (vice-chairwoman), J\u00f6rg Dr\u00e4ger and [[Brigitte Mohn]].<ref name=\"Organisation\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/ueber-uns/wer-wir-sind/organisation/|title=Organisation|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2018-01-12|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nThe executive board is advised and supervised by the Bertelsmann Stiftung board of trustees. This is involved in all decisions of fundamental importance. Its tasks also include approving the annual financial statements, overseeing the foundation's business management and formally accepting and approving the executive board's statement of activities. According to the bylaws, the board of trustees has at least six and a maximum of 14 members. These include the chairman or another member of the [[supervisory board]] of the Bertelsmann Group; a successor to Bertelsmann Stiftung founder Reinhard Mohn; Liz Mohn; and three to 11 other persons.<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> The Bertelsmann Stiftung board of trustees currently includes Werner J. Bauer (chairman), Liz Mohn (vice-chairwoman), Wolf Bauer, Carsten Coesfeld,<ref>{{cite news|language=de|title=Achten Sie auf \u2026 Carsten Coesfeld|newspaper=Manager Magazin|number=8|year=2008|url=http://heft.manager-magazin.de/MM/2018/8/158462564/index.html|access-date={{date|2018-07-20|mdy}}}}</ref> [[Thomas Buberl]], Ulrike Detmers,<ref>{{cite news |language=de |title=Neues Mitglied in namhaftem Kreis |newspaper=G\u00fctersloher Zeitung |date={{date|2017-10-25|mdy}} |page=10}}</ref> Ralph Heck, Wolfgang A. Herrmann, Christoph Mohn, Carolina M\u00fcller-M\u00f6hl, [[Viviane Reding]], [[Philipp R\u00f6sler]],<ref>{{cite news |language=de |title=Philipp R\u00f6sler im Kuratorium |newspaper=Die Glocke |date={{date|2017-12-22|mdy}} |page=17}}</ref> and J\u00fcrgen Stark.<ref name=\"Organisation\" />\n\n=== Funding ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung is funded primarily by dividends from the Bertelsmann Group. In the 2018 [[Fiscal year|financial year]], funding from this source totaled \u20ac120.8 million, or 96% of the revenues.<ref name=\"Finance\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Publikationen/Infomaterialien/IN_Jahresbericht_2018_DE_2019_03_01.pdf|language=de|format=PDF|title=Finanzen|website=Jahresbericht 2018|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|access-date={{date|2019-03-05|mdy}}|pages=6\u20139}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung holds its shares in the Bertelsmann Group indirectly through ''Johannes Mohn GmbH'', in which it holds a majority interest. The foundation's Bertelsmann Group shares are solely capital shares; voting rights are held by the ''Bertelsmann Verwaltungsgesellschaft mbH''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reinhard Mohn verzichtet auf seine Stimmrechte|date={{date|1999-07-02|mdy}}|page=13|language=de|newspaper=B\u00f6rsen-Zeitung}}</ref> Additional funding comes from partnerships with other non-profit organizations, income from the foundation's assets and donations. The Bertelsmann Stiftung sets aside reserves&nbsp;as required by the relevant tax regulations in order to pursue its activities independently of current income.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hilfe f\u00fcr die klammen Kommunen: 40 Millionen Euro in die R\u00fccklage|date={{date|2015-05-06|mdy}}|page=25|language=de|author=Lothar Schmalen|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> In the 2018 financial year, these reserves amounted to \u20ac492 million.<ref name=\"Finance\" />\n\nSince its establishment, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has invested a total of \u20ac1.5 billion in charitable work. In the 2018 financial year, expenditures amounted to around \u20ac86.2 million. The majority (\u20ac49.0 million) was spent on programs and special projects; \u20ac11.6 million were spent on administrative activities, \u20ac6.8 million on communication and \u20ac4.7 million on project-related services. In addition, the Bertelsmann Stiftung made grants to affiliated [[Nonprofit organization|non-profit organizations]] in the amount of \u20ac14.2 million.<ref name=\"Finance\" />\n\n=== Locations ===\n[[File:Postkarte_Nebenstelle_Reichsbank_Moltkestra\u00dfe_G\u00fctersloh.jpg|thumb|Reichsbank branch in G\u00fctersloh (historical postcard motif)]]\n\nThe first offices of the Bertelsmann Stiftung were located in a residential building on G\u00fctersloh's Carl-Miele-Stra\u00dfe. In 1980, offices were rented from the Bertelsmann Group instead. In 1986, the Bertelsmann Stiftung moved to a historic building on Moltkestra\u00dfe, which had been erected by a subsidiary of the [[Reichsbank]] in 1893 and was owned by the central bank of the state of North Rhine-Westphalia until 1985.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> In 1989, the architecture firm [[Gerkan, Marg and Partners]] won a competition to design the new headquarters of the Bertelsmann Stiftung opposite the headquarters of the Bertelsmann Group.<ref name=\"Gerkan, Mang und Partner\" /> The building was completed in 1990 and expanded several times over the following years.<ref name=\"Chronicle\" /> In addition to the head office in G\u00fctersloh, the Bertelsmann Group has an office in the Kommandantenhaus in Berlin, which is also used by the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kommandantur wird nachgebaut|date={{date|2000-11-21|mdy}}|page=23|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Das Kommandantenhaus kehrt zur\u00fcck|date={{date|1999-09-29|mdy}}|page=14|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Terrakotta-Adler im Anflug auf das Kommandantenhaus|date={{date|2003-06-13|mdy}}|page=35|language=de|author=Konrad Jahr|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref> Furthermore, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has an office in the [[Brussels and the European Union#European Quarter|European Quarter]] in [[City of Brussels|Brussels]].<ref>{{cite web|language=de|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Publikationen/Infomaterialien/IN_Jahresbericht_2017_DE_2018-03-08.pdf|title=Standorte|website=Jahresbericht 2018|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|page=11|access-date={{date|2018-03-15|mdy}}|format=PDF}}</ref>\n\nIn the mid-1990s, the Fundaci\u00f3n Bertelsmann, an independent subsidiary foundation, was established in [[Barcelona]], the capital of Catalonia. The aim was to promote reading and media literacy in Spain.<ref>{{cite book|title=Schl\u00fcsselmomente: Erfahrungen eines engagierten Lebens|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2011|isbn=978-3-641-07123-3|location=M\u00fcnchen|page=97|language=de|author=Liz Mohn}}</ref> Today, the Fundaci\u00f3n Bertelsmann focuses on vocational training and career guidance for young people in Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/index.php?id=4056|title=Fundaci\u00f3n Bertelsmann|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nSince 2008, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has also been represented in US-capital [[Washington, D.C.|Washington, D.C]], by a second independent foundation, the Bertelsmann Foundation North America, which addresses challenges relating to transatlantic partnerships.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Stiftung zieht\u2019s nach Washington|date={{date|2008-04-16|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Schl\u00fcsselmomente: Erfahrungen eines engagierten Lebens|publisher=C. Bertelsmann Verlag|year=2011|isbn=978-3-641-07123-3|location=M\u00fcnchen|page=30|language=de|author=Liz Mohn}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/index.php?id=4057|title=Bertelsmann Foundation North America|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-12-12|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n== Activities ==\nAccording to its bylaws, the purpose of the Bertelsmann Stiftung is to \"promote science and research, religion, public health, youth and elderly welfare, art and culture, public and professional education, social welfare, an international perspective, democracy and social engagement.\"<ref name=\"Satzung\" /> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is a private operating foundation and does not make grants.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fingerzeige aus der Denkfabrik|date={{date|2014-04-30|mdy}}|page=12|language=de|author=Thorsten G\u00f6decker|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sch\u00fcssel: Kurator in deutscher Stiftung|date={{date|2007-04-20|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=Die Presse}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung \u2013 Info|date={{date|2010-11-03|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Rheinische Post}}</ref> It invests funds in projects that it conceives, initiates and implements itself.<ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|page=295|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2007/46/Bertelsmann|title=Wo geht es hier zur Zukunft?|date={{date|2007-11-11|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Zeit|author=G\u00f6tz Hamann}}</ref> For example, the Bertelsmann Stiftung produces studies and rankings,<ref>{{cite news|title=Eine Studie der Bertelsmann-Stiftung: Lesen im multimedialen Zeitalter|date={{date|1994-03-04|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung|author=Anna Katharina Ulrich}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Wirtschaftsstandort Deutschland unter Beschuss|date={{date|2004-10-08|mdy}}|page=28|language=de|newspaper=Wiener Zeitung}}</ref> conducts model projects,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bessere Bildungschancen f\u00fcr sozial Schwache|date={{date|2010-02-24|mdy}}|page=30|language=de|newspaper=Heilbronner Stimme}}</ref> shares knowledge and expertise,<ref>{{cite news|title=Orientierung im Dschungel der Medizin|date={{date|2008-06-05|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Stern|author=Thomas Osterkorn}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Von Verkaufsrhetorik bis Yoga: Volkshochschule pr\u00e4sentiert neues Programm; Zusammenarbeit mit Bertelsmann-Stiftung|date={{date|2000-09-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=S\u00fcdkurier}}</ref> organizes congresses and awards prizes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Symposium der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2000-09-07|mdy}}|page=1|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Ein Preis f\u00fcr die Schule der Zukunft|date={{date|2000-05-29|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Passauer Neue Presse}}</ref> Key fields are education, democracy, social affairs, health, the economy and culture.<ref>{{cite news|title=De Geus wird Chef der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2012-08-07|mdy}}|page=46|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung does not engage in partisan politics.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung setzt sich f\u00fcr das Gemeinwohl ein|date={{date|2008-01-19|mdy}}|edition=Bad Homburg|page=7|language=de|newspaper=Taunus-Zeitung}}</ref> It works regionally, nationally and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/unsere-projekte/|title=Unsere Projekte|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Gemeinwohl und Eigeninteresse: Das globale Engagement der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2007-03-30|mdy}}|page=68|language=de|author=Rudolph Bauer|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref>\n\n=== Education ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung examines at regular intervals how much the [[States of Germany|Germany's states]] are investing in early childhood education and care. One of its studies confirmed, for instance, that children's developmental opportunities depend heavily on their background.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2008/24/C-Interview-Stein/komplettansicht|title=Der Kita-Report|date={{date|2008-06-05|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|author=Jeannette Otto|newspaper=Die Zeit}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.taz.de/!5314782/|title=Zweiter Platz f\u00fcr Bremen|date={{date|2016-06-29|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung|author=J\u00f6rdis Fr\u00fcchtenicht}}</ref> In the field of school education, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been devoting itself in recent years to [[all-day school]]s in particular and has called for their expansion.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mehr Ganztagsschulen|date={{date|2013-08-05|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Osnabr\u00fccker Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Gutes Zeugnis f\u00fcr Ganztagsschulen|date={{date|2016-09-20|mdy}}|page=11|language=de|newspaper=Berliner Morgenpost}}</ref> Digital learning is also an important issue,<ref>{{cite news|title=Digitales Lernen scheitert oft am WLAN|date={{date|2016-08-26|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> as it is seen as a solution to various structural problems in the area of education.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lernen lernen und Kenner kennen|date={{date|2015-10-12|mdy}}|pages=92\u201393|language=de|newspaper=Profil|author=Michaela Ernst}}</ref> In addition, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has also been involved for years in vocational education and training.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung mit Angebot zur beruflichen Weiterbildung|date={{date|1994-06-23|mdy}}|page=83|language=de|author=Christian G\u00fcntlisberger|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref>\n\nIn the 1990s, the Bertelsmann Stiftung's activities in the area of higher education&nbsp;received particularly widespread public attention,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung will die Bildungspolitik pr\u00e4gen|date={{date|1998-12-10|mdy}}|page=6|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> for example the establishment of the ''Centre for Higher Education (CHE)'' in 1994 by the Bertelsmann Stiftung and the [[German Rectors' Conference]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Verbraucherzentrale f\u00fcr die Unis: Das Centrum f\u00fcr Hochschulentwicklung in G\u00fctersloh nimmt die Arbeit auf|date={{date|1994-03-03|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel|author=Thomas Veser}}</ref> This institution sees itself as a \"workshop\" for developing reforms for Germany\u2019s&nbsp;higher education institutions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeit.de/2000/07/200007.artikel_44_.xml|title=Ein Grund zum Feiern|date={{date|2000-02-10|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Zeit|author=Sabine Etzold}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Der Meister-Ranker|date={{date|2005-05-22|mdy}}|page=78|language=de|newspaper=NZZ am Sonntag}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung holds 90% of the shares in ''CHE Gemeinn\u00fctziges Centrum f\u00fcr Hochschulentwicklung GmbH''.<ref name=\"Unternehmensregister\">{{cite web|url=https://www.unternehmensregister.de/|title=Unternehmensregister|publisher=Bundesanzeiger Verlag|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n=== Democracy ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung is committed on both the national and the international level to strengthening democracy through the promotion of citizen participation in political decision-making and planning processes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mehr direkte Demokratie|date={{date|2014-09-05|mdy}}|page=22|language=de|author=Simone Lutz|newspaper=Badische Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mehr B\u00fcrgerbeteiligung st\u00e4rkt die Demokratie|date={{date|2014-09-06|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Aachener Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung w\u00fcrdigt B\u00fcrgerbeteiligung in Brasilien|date={{date|2011-06-16|mdy}}|language=de|author=dapd Nachrichtenagentur}}</ref> With regard to cooperation between Germany's federal government, state and local institutions, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been calling for several years for a revision of the system used to redistribute income among the country's states.<ref>{{cite news|title=Entmachtung der Bundesl\u00e4nder|date={{date|2012-09-28|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|author=Jens Tartler|newspaper=Financial Times Deutschland}}</ref> The focus of the foundation's work in the field of democracy, however, is [[Europe]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Schwerpunkt Europa: Bertelsmann Stiftung reagiert auf kritische Umfrageergebnisse|date={{date|2012-09-17|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Europa im Fokus der Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2016-05-19|mdy}}|page=1|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> For years, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has advocated accelerating the [[European Union|EU]]'s decision-making processes and promoting [[European integration]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung pl\u00e4diert f\u00fcr eine Beschleunigung der Entscheidungsprozesse \u2013 Europa braucht eine Stimme und ein Gesicht \u2013 Br\u00fcsseler Kommission sollte verkleinert und gest\u00e4rkt werden|date={{date|2006-06-19|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Agra-Europe}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Europa weiterbauen: Bertelsmann Stiftung stellt Jahresplanung vor|date={{date|2013-05-01|mdy}}|language=de|author=Bernhard Hertlein|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> Internationally, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is researching existing governance structures and developing proposals to change them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thielen trifft Ban Ki-Moon: Internationale Konferenz der Bertelsmann Stiftung in Berlin|date={{date|2008-07-18|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung kooperiert mit Institut f\u00fcr Weltwirtschaft|date={{date|2011-04-19|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> One example is the concept of a non-profit rating agency.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ideen f\u00fcr neue Rating-Agentur|date={{date|2012-04-18|mdy}}|page=33|language=de|author=Matthias Benz|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref>\n\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung also helped fund the ''Center for Applied Policy Research (CAP)'' in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.taz.de/!220824/|title=Abgang des Vorzeige-Bertelsmanns|date={{date|2007-10-31|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung|author=Max H\u00e4gler}}</ref> The center was founded by Werner Weidenfeld, who was also a member of the Bertelsmann Stiftung executive board until 2007.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ende einer wunderbaren Freundschaft|date={{date|2007-11-01|mdy}}|page=27|language=de|author=Peter Dittmar|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|pages=320\u2013326|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref> Both institutions cooperated on a number of issues, including European integration.<ref>{{cite news|title=Europa, die komplizierte Grossbaustelle|date={{date|1999-09-27|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung|author=Martin Breitenstein}}</ref> The center is affiliated with the Geschwister Scholl Institute of Political Science at [[Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cap-lmu.de/cap/|title=Strategien f\u00fcr das 21. Jahrhundert|publisher=Centrum f\u00fcr angewandte Politikforschung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\n=== Society ===\nOne major focus of the work done by the Bertelsmann Stiftung is demographic change in Germany, a subject on which it has published several studies.<ref>{{cite news|title=Studie: Hamburg f\u00fcr die Zukunft gut ger\u00fcstet|date={{date|2007-02-12|mdy}}|page=31|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Osten leidet besonders|date={{date|2011-03-24|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> It also promotes volunteer work and other activities that increase social cohesion,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/themen/gesellschaft-entwickeln/engagement-und-zusammenhalt/|title=Engagement und Zusammenhalt|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> in part by awarding of the \"Mein gutes Beispiel\" (My Best Practice) prize.<ref>{{cite news|title=Preis f\u00fcr Regionalmarketing|date={{date|2013-02-28|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Passauer Neue Presse}}</ref> Social justice and intergenerational equity are also important concerns,<ref>{{cite news|title=Soziale Gerechtigkeit als Zahl|date={{date|2011-01-04|mdy}}|page=24|language=de|author=Beat Gygi|newspaper=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung}}</ref> and one of the reasons the foundation addresses these subjects is to narrow the gap between rich and poor.<ref>{{cite news|title=Viel Nachholbedarf bei der sozialen Gerechtigkeit|date={{date|2011-01-06|mdy}}|page=5|language=de|author=Alexander Jungkunz|newspaper=N\u00fcrnberger Nachrichten}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Foundation wants to promote social integration and diversity. It advocates for creating a \"comprehensive and long-term migration architecture\" for Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fr-online.de/meinung/gastbeitrag-einwanderung-schluss-mit--einwanderung-als-ausnahme-,1472602,25000202.html|title=Schluss mit Einwanderung als Ausnahme|date={{date|2013-11-11|mdy}}|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=J\u00f6rg Dr\u00e4ger}}</ref> Other projects address young people and families. For example, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is critical of the increase in [[child poverty]] in Germany and the way the country's pension system disadvantages families.<ref>{{cite news|title=Studie: Rentenversicherung benachteiligt Familien|date={{date|2014-01-18|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Osnabr\u00fccker Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/2016-09/kinderarmut-deutschland-hartz-iv|title=Kinderarmut nimmt in Deutschland zu|date={{date|2016-09-12|mdy}}|website=Zeit Online|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Andreas Gebert}}</ref>\n\n=== Health ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung regularly analyzed health care in Germany for what it calls its \"Gesundheitsmonitor\" (Health-Care Monitor).<ref>{{cite news|title=Zuzahlungen \u00fcberfordern Versicherte|date={{date|2006-04-25|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Th\u00fcringer Allgemeine}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung legt Gesundheitsmonitor vor \u2013 Krankenversicherte wollen Preisbindung bei Medizin|date={{date|2010-03-12|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> Moreover, it has launched several projects in the last few years that promote informed decision-making among the public in the area of [[health care]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/themen/gesundheit-aktivieren/|title=Gesundheit aktivieren|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012154702/http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/de/themen/gesundheit-aktivieren/|archive-date=October 12, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The projects include the Internet portal \"Wei\u00dfe Liste\" (White List) which helps users find the doctor, hospital, nursing home or nursing service that is right for them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wei\u00dfe Liste f\u00fcr Kliniken: Neue Internetplattform hilft Patienten, das f\u00fcr sie richtige und beste Krankenhaus zu finden|date={{date|2008-06-05|mdy}}|page=31|language=de|newspaper=Die Welt|author=Pia Heinemann}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Wegweiser im Pflege-Dschungel|date={{date|2013-02-01|mdy}}|language=de|author=Judith Lacroix|newspaper=Darmst\u00e4dter Echo}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Neues Vergleichsportal f\u00fcr Heime|date={{date|2016-06-27|mdy}}|page=16|language=de|newspaper=N\u00fcrnberger Nachrichten}}</ref>\n\nWith the support of the Bertelsmann Stiftung, the Center for Hospital Management (CKM) was founded in 1994 as a research institute at the [[University of M\u00fcnster]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung: Sieben Millionen DM f\u00fcr innovative Medizinprojekte|date={{date|2000-11-02|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte-Zeitung}}</ref> In addition to research on clinical IT and logistics, the center organizes training for the clinic's staff.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kurse in M\u00fcnster: Reha-Manager werden Strategen im Wettbewerb|date={{date|1998-05-04|mdy}}|page=13|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte-Zeitung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vom Praxischef zum Gesundheitsmanager|date={{date|2004-12-08|mdy}}|page=24|language=de|newspaper=\u00c4rzte-Zeitung}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is no longer one of the shareholders of the ''CKM Centrum f\u00fcr Krankenhausmanagement GmbH.''<ref name=\"Unternehmensregister\" /> The institute has become a completely independent organization.<ref>{{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-40832-3|location=Frankfurt am Main|pages=458\u2013459|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}</ref>\n\n=== Culture ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung's oldest project in the field of culture is the competition [[Neue Stimmen]] (New Voices) international singing competition,<ref>{{cite news|title=Neue Stimmen im Wettstreit|date={{date|1991-10-31|mdy}}|page=17|language=de|newspaper=Bonner General-Anzeiger}}</ref> which was launched by Liz Mohn in 1987 and still takes place today.<ref>{{cite news|title=Musik geh\u00f6rt zu meinem Leben|date={{date|2013-03-13|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Neue Stimmen in der Stadt|date={{date|2011-10-20|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> It is one of the world's most important competitions for up-and-coming opera singers and is known as a \"showcase for new talent.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Neue Stimmen f\u00fcr die Oper|date={{date|2002-12-17|mdy}}|page=11|language=de|newspaper=Berliner Kurier}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Meisterkurse offen f\u00fcr Besucher|date={{date|2016-10-06|mdy}}|page=13|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung promotes an engagement with music in other ways as well. Model projects in this area have been carried out repeatedly since the end of the 1990s to achieve a number of objectives, including more and better [[music education]] in [[preschool]]s.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mit Musik zu besserer Leistung|date={{date|1999-08-13|mdy}}|page=28|language=de|author=Gudrun Weitzenb\u00fcrger|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Drei neue Caddys f\u00fcr Mika|date={{date|2014-09-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mit Musik lernen Kinder besser sprechen|date={{date|2016-12-13|mdy}}|page=26|language=de|author=J\u00f6rg Janssen|newspaper=Rheinische Post}}</ref> The goal is to increase social participation through singing and music.<ref>{{cite news|title=Singen: Hymne der Woche|date={{date|2001-12-23|mdy}}|page=34|language=de|newspaper=Welt am Sonntag}}</ref>\n\n=== Economy ===\nThe foundation has examined the impact of globalization on society is examined in terms of the opportunities and risks it presents.<ref>{{cite news|title=Globalisierung hilft Reichen \u2013 Deutschland geh\u00f6rt laut der Bertelsmann Stiftung zu den Gewinnern der weltweiten Verflechtung|date={{date|2014-03-25|mdy}}|page=19|language=de|newspaper=Badische Zeitung}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung advocates for developed countries to open their markets so that emerging economies can benefit more from economic developments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeit.de/wirtschaft/2016-09/weltwirtschaft-globalisierung-bertelsmann-schwellenlaender-industrielaender-handelsabkommen-thiess-petersen|title=Die Industriel\u00e4nder m\u00fcssen ihre M\u00e4rkte \u00f6ffnen|date={{date|2016-09-02|mdy}}|website=Zeit Online|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Jakob Pontius}}</ref> It has repeatedly published analyses and studies on changes in the German labor market,<ref>{{cite news|title=Der gro\u00dfe Deutschland-Check|date={{date|2002-04-04|mdy}}|page=16|language=de|author=Rainer H\u00fcbner|newspaper=Capital}}</ref> and the findings were partly incorporated into the Hartz reforms carried out during the [[Gerhard Schr\u00f6der]] government.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/unternehmen/it-medien/enthuellungsbuch-schlimme-vorwuerfe-gegen-bertelsmann-stiftung/3513246.html|title=Schlimme Vorw\u00fcrfe gegen Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2010-08-11|mdy}}|website=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Think-tanks in Germany: The Bertelsmann Foundations's Role in Labour Market Reform|year=2008|pages=437\u2013457|language=en|author=Hartwig Pautz|newspaper=Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Politikberatung|number=3/4}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is also committed to promoting sustainability and ensuring German businesses act in a socially responsible manner.<ref>{{cite news|title=L\u00e4nder-Stresstest: Deutschland bei Nachhaltigkeit nur gut|date={{date|2015-09-09|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Th\u00fcringer Allgemeine}}</ref> In collaboration with the [[Hans B\u00f6ckler|Hans B\u00f6ckler Foundation]], it carried out a study on employee participation in German companies.<ref>{{cite news|title=Miteinander statt gegeneinander zum Erfolg|date={{date|1994-09-30|mdy}}|page=2|language=de|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Stark in Unternehmenskultur|date={{date|2004-10-01|mdy}}|page=16|language=de|newspaper=Junge Karriere}}</ref>\n\n== Criticism ==\nIn recent years, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been the subject of public debate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmannkritik.de/|title=Bertelsmannkritik|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref> In 2007, Jens Wernicke and Torsten Bultmann published an anthology, entitled \"Netzwerk der Macht \u2013 Bertelsmann\" (\"Network of Power \u2013 Bertelsmann\"),<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung kritisch im Blick|date={{date|2007-03-29|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> which takes a critical look at the structure and activities of the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nichts Neues? Da irrt Liz Mohn|date={{date|2007-05-22|mdy}}|page=3|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> The book's 30 contributors focused in particular on the foundation's non-profit status and [[Power (social and political)|political influence]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.handelsblatt.com/mediawatcher/2007/05/24/autoren-greifen-bertelsmann-stiftung-an/|title=Autoren greifen Bertelsmann Stiftung an|date={{date|2007-05-24|mdy}}|website=Medienwatcher|publisher=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter-Siebenhaar}}</ref> The anthology generated widespread public debate on the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Debatte \u00fcber Bertelsmann bef\u00f6rdert|date={{date|2007-08-03|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\nPublished in 2010, the book \"Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland \u2013 eine Stiftung macht Politik\" (\"Bertelsmann's Republic of Germany: A Foundation Sets Policy\") by author and journalist Thomas Schuler gained even greater attention.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deutschlandfunk.de/nur-im-eigenen-interesse.1310.de.html?dram:article_id=194162|title=Nur im eigenen Interesse|date={{date|2010-08-23|mdy}}|website=Deutschlandfunk|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Ralph Gerstenberg}}</ref> In it, Schuler describes how the Bertelsmann Stiftung seeks to make contact with leading politicians and to [[Political consulting|advise]] them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Schuler schreibt \u00fcber Bertelsmannrepublik|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> He criticized the Bertelsmann Stiftung as being \"undemocratic\" and lacking in transparency.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Stiftung ist undemokratisch|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bei Fragen zu Details stie\u00df ich an Grenzen|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt}}</ref> In his opinion, the originally good idea behind the foundation developed into a \"distorted world,\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Wahrheiten und Gemeinheiten|date={{date|2010-08-20|mdy}}|page=57|language=de|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> the basic organization of which he called into question.<ref>{{cite news|title=Politik aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2010-09-13|mdy}}|page=7|language=de|author=Harald Schumann|newspaper=Der Tagesspiegel}}</ref> Schuler also criticized German foundation law, which allows foundations such as the Bertelsmann Stiftung to exist at all.<ref name=\"2010-08-09\" /> Peter Rawert, an expert on foundations, noted that the Bertelsmann Stiftung is guaranteed a return on its holdings in the Bertelsmann Group that is probably lower than what could be achieved with a [[Fixed income|fixed-income]] [[investment]]. He also noted that in the United States this would have a negative impact on the foundation's non-profit tax status; moreover, he argued that the situation does not reflect the \"standard of efficiency\" normally endorsed by the Bertelsmann Stiftung.<ref>{{cite news|title=Grundg\u00fctiges aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2010-09-14|mdy}}|page=35|language=de|newspaper=Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung}}</ref>\n\n=== Commercial interests ===\nDue to its majority interest in the Bertelsmann Group, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has been repeatedly accused of combining [[non-profit]] and [[profit (economics)|commercial interests]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deutschlandradiokultur.de/die-guetersloher-nebenregierung.950.de.html?dram:article_id=139101|title=Die G\u00fctersloher Nebenregierung|date={{date|2010-08-31|mdy}}|website=Deutschlandradio Kultur|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Vera Lin\u00df}}</ref> In 2009, the journalist and author Annette Jensen asserted that the Bertelsmann Stiftung's proposals [[demand generation|generate artificial demand]], particularly in terms of the purported need to [[Small government|streamline local government]], a demand which the foundation then meets, for example through the Bertelsmann subsidiary [[Arvato]]. She suggested that the [[RTL Television|RTL]] and [[VOX (German TV channel)|VOX]] television stations belonging to the Bertelsmann Group and numerous [[Gruner + Jahr]] magazines served the foundation by disseminating its messages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://publik.verdi.de/2009/ausgabe_01_02/gesellschaft/.gesellschaft/seite_9/A0|title=Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeit ist ein gutes Gesch\u00e4ft|date=2009|website=ver.di Publik|publisher=Vereinte Dienstleistungsgewerkschaft|page=9|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Annette Jensen}}</ref> The sociologist and entrepreneur Frank Adloff has argued that it is indefensible that the foundation does not need to justify the use of its funds before any parliament or oversight authority. In the United States, he noted, non-profit foundations are not permitted to hold more than a 20% stake in a company in order to avoid possible [[conflict of interest|conflicts of interest]]; in addition, they have to provide a [[public accounting]] of their expenditures.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\" />\n\n=== Political influence ===\nAnother criticism involves a lack of [[Legitimacy (political)|democratic legitimacy]]. Commenting on the foundation's \"engagement with civil society,\" Wolfgang Lieb, former state secretary in the North Rhine-Westphalia [[Ministry of Science]], has argued that this legitimacy is being increasingly diminished, and even replaced by, [[economic power]]. According to Lieb, private networks and behind-the-scenes advisors are thus turning into actual rulers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nachdenkseiten.de/?p=2144|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung und ihre Verflechtungen / Referat im Rahmen einer Vortragsreihe des Rosa-Luxemburg-Clubs Wuppertal|date={{date|2007-02-26|mdy}}|website=Nachdenkseiten|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Wolfgang Lieb}}</ref> By consulting with politicians outside of government settings, Lieb suggests, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is pursuing a \"[[privatization]] of politics,\" a situation that offers mutual benefits: [[civil servant]]s and politicians are given a protected space where they alone are provided with information free of charge and where they can engage in discussion, while the Bertelsmann Stiftung secures access to all the projects it wants to influence. Thus, no matter who is elected, the Bertelsmann Stiftung is always part of the government.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\" /> Speaking with broadcaster [[Deutschlandfunk]] in 2007, the former [[Social Democratic Party of Germany|SPD]] politician and publicist Albrecht M\u00fcller called the foundation an \"[[anti-democratic]] institution.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nachdenkseiten.de/?p=2231|title=Deutschlandfunk Zwischent\u00f6ne als Audio \u2013 Ein Experiment bei den Nachdenkseiten (Mitschnitt der Sendung)|date={{date|2007-04-03|mdy}}|website=Nachdenkseiten|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the journalist and politician Julika Sandt criticized the growing influence of the Bertelsmann Stiftung on [[German health care]], saying that initiatives developed by the foundation lead to preferential treatment for [[privatized clinic]]s and medical care centers to the detriment of self-employed physicians. According to Sandt, because Brigitte Mohn is a member of both the Bertelsmann Stiftung executive board and the supervisory board of [[Rh\u00f6n-Klinikum]], the foundation's neutrality in the health sector is questionable.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bzb-online.de/apr08/10_11.pdf|title=F\u00e4den der Macht: Die Bertelsmann-Connection und das Ende der Freiberuflichkeit|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|year=2008|pages=10\u201311|language=de|format=PDF|newspaper=Bayerisches Zahn\u00e4rzteblatt|author=Julika Sandt}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Josef Kraus, president of the {{ill|German Teachers' Association|de|Deutscher Lehrerverband}}, spoke critically about the influence of the Bertelsmann Stiftung on [[education policy]]. He described its studies as \"[[unscientific]]\" and as \"[[scare tactics]].\" Its activities almost always involved turning some alleged administrative failure into a scandal, Kraus said. He called on politicians to stop allowing themselves to be influenced by the Bertelsmann Stiftung and to take criticism of the foundation seriously.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lehrerverband.de/aktuell_Dossier_Bertelsmannstudien_Dez_12.html|title=\u00dcber den Wert von Bertelsmann-Studien|date=December 2012|publisher=Deutscher Lehrerverband|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Josef Kraus|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702113018/http://www.lehrerverband.de/aktuell_Dossier_Bertelsmannstudien_Dez_12.html|archive-date=July 2, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe non-profit organization Lobbycontrol sees the Bertelsmann Stiftung as a business-oriented initiative, similar to the \"[[Initiative Neue Soziale Marktwirtschaft]]\" (Initiative for a New Social Market Economy) or the \"[[Stiftung Marktwirtschaft]]\" (Free Market Foundation).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lobbypedia.de/wiki/Bertelsmann_Stiftung|title=Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2016-12-20|mdy}}|website=Lobbycontrol|language=de|access-date={{date|2017-03-06|mdy}}}}</ref> Lobbycontrol criticizes, for example, the \"Standortcheck\" (Business Location Check), which it says amounts to a canonical neoliberal reform.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.socialtimes.de/nachricht.php?nachricht_id=7704&newsrubrik_id=6|title=B\u00fcrgerrechtler kritisieren Bertelsmann Stiftung|website=Social Times|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928063204/http://www.socialtimes.de/nachricht.php?nachricht_id=7704&newsrubrik_id=6|archive-date={{date|2007-09-28|mdy}}|url-status = dead|access-date={{date|2017-03-06|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung has repeatedly refuted criticism asserting a lack of democratic legitimacy and unpermitted political influence. For example, Gunter Thielen, former chairman and CEO of the Bertelsmann Stiftung, made it clear that the foundation was not a \"secret government,\" that the formation of public opinion and policy is not a \"top-down process,\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/unternehmen/it-medien/gunter-thielen-wir-sind-keine-heimliche-regierung/3572788.html|title=Wir sind keine heimliche Regierung|date={{date|2010-10-25|mdy}}|website=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar}}</ref> and that it was unimaginable that a foundation or a company could use its own ideas to influence or control a country like the Federal Republic of Germany.<ref name=\"2010-08-09\">{{cite web|url=http://www.taz.de/!5137692/|title=Politischer Einfluss illusorisch|date={{date|2010-08-09|mdy}}|website=Die Tageszeitung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Steffen Grimberg}}</ref>\n\n=== Political neutrality ===\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung describes itself as politically non-partisan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/fileadmin/files/BSt/Publikationen/Infomaterialien/IN_BSt_Auf_einenBlick_D_2015.pdf|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung auf einen Blick|publisher=Bertelsmann Stiftung|language=de|format=PDF|access-date={{date|2017-01-31|mdy}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.die-glocke.de/lokalnachrichten/kreisguetersloh/guetersloh/Piraten-kritisieren-Bertelsmann-Stiftung-79136bfe-bce7-4e4d-a32d-f0ff4644d2e0-ds|title=Piraten kritisieren Bertelsmann Stiftung|date={{date|2016-12-02|mdy}}|website=Die Glocke|language=de|access-date={{date|2017-01-31|mdy}}}}</ref> The practical implementation of this principle, however, has been questioned from several sides, in particular because the foundation has only established contacts with \"radical supporters of market policies\" among left-leaning parties.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\" /> In turn, the Bertelsmann Stiftung has often been characterized as a proponent of [[economic liberalism]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Abkehr von der Globalisierung|date={{date|2016-09-01|mdy}}|page=1|language=de|author=Wolfgang B\u00f6hm|newspaper=Die Presse}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=B\u00fcrgergesellschaft als Projekt: Eine Bestandsaufnahme zu Entwicklung und F\u00f6rderung zivilgesellschaftlicher Potenziale in Deutschland|publisher=Verlag f\u00fcr Sozialwissenschaften|year=2009|isbn=978-3-531-16266-9|editor=Ansgar Klein |editor2=Ralf Kleinfeld |editor3=Frank Nullmeier |editor4=Dieter Rucht |editor5=Heike Walk |editor6=Ulrich Willems |editor7=Annette Zimmer |display-editors=3|location=Wiesbaden|page=288|language=de|newspaper=B\u00fcrgergesellschaft und Demokratie}}</ref> but this is also controversial;<ref>{{cite book|title=Politikberatung und die Herstellung von Entscheidungssicherheit im politischen System|publisher=Verlag f\u00fcr Sozialwissenschaften|year=2008|isbn=978-3-531-16048-1|location=Wiesbaden|page=236|language=de|author=Isabel Kusche}}</ref> some critics have also labeled the Bertelsmann Stiftung [[Neoliberalism|neoliberal]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Wo bleiben die Visionen?|date={{date|2009-11-12|mdy}}|page=4|language=de|author=G\u00fcnter Bihn|newspaper=Frankfurter Rundschau}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Supermarkt Europa: Vom Ausverkauf unserer Demokratie|publisher=Czernin Verlag|year=2014|isbn=978-3-7076-0521-1|location=Wien|page=15|language=de|author=Robert Misik, Michel Reimon}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bonzen, Bildung, Bertelsmann \u2013 Die Bertelsmann Stiftung als Denkfabrik des Neoliberalismus|date={{date|2005-11-18|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Analyse und Kritik|number=500}}</ref>\n\n=== Non-profit status ===\nIn 2006, the author and journalist Harald Schumann discussed the non-profit status of the Bertelsmann Stiftung in the [[Der Tagesspiegel|Tagesspiegel]] newspaper. According to Schumann, the \"[[deep state|shadow government]] in G\u00fctersloh\" runs on de facto on public money, because Reinhard Mohn saved an over \u20ac2 billion euros in [[inheritance tax|inheritance]] and [[gift tax]]es when he transferred three-quarters of the Bertelsmann Group capital shares to the foundation. Moreover, he asserts, the annual dividend payment to the foundation is tax-free and, with its annual budget of around \u20ac60 million, the foundation does not spend nearly as much as it costs the state in terms of lost revenue.<ref name=\"2006-09-24\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tagesspiegel.de/zeitung/macht-ohne-mandat/755580.html|title=Macht ohne Mandat|date={{date|2006-09-24|mdy}}|website=Der Tagesspiegel|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Harald Schumann}}</ref> Arno Kl\u00f6nne, a sociologist and political scientist, has argued that the Bertelsmann Stiftung's non-profit nature was questionable because, he maintains, it actively promotes the business of the Bertelsmann Group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.handelsblatt.com/mediawatcher/2007/06/11/ist-die-bertelsmann-stiftung-noch-gemeinnutzig/|title=Ist die Bertelsmann Stiftung noch gemeinn\u00fctzig?|date={{date|2007-06-11|mdy}}|website=Medienwatcher|publisher=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=G\u00fctersloher Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeiten|date={{date|2007-10-31|mdy}}|page=10|language=de|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar|newspaper=Handelsblatt}}</ref> Ultimately, he suggests, its goal is to manage society using corporate methods and to [[Privatization|privatize]] the tasks that should be handled by the state.<ref>{{cite news|title=Im Sitzen durchs Netzwerk|date={{date|2007-06-09|mdy}}|language=de|author=Stefan Brams|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, a group of independent legal experts found that the Bertelsmann Stiftung no longer met the requirements for a non-profit organization. On the contrary, they argued, the [[tax exemption]] was unjustly being used for the purpose of carrying out a transformation of society according to the beliefs of the Bertelsmann Stiftung's founder, Reinhard Mohn, by means of private, tax-financed private policy consulting and by bypassing democratic decision making processes through public discourse in Germany's constitutional bodies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrhz.de/flyer/beitrag.php?id=13431|title=Ist die Bertelsmann Stiftung \"gemeinn\u00fctzig\" im Sinne von \u00a7\u00a7 52 ff. AO? Eine Expertise unabh\u00e4ngiger Juristen.|date={{date|2009-02-04|mdy}}|website=Neue Rheinische Zeitung|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}}}</ref>\n\nThe Bertelsmann Stiftung has always rejected these accusations, noting that its non-profit status has been recognized by the tax authorities and is reviewed on an ongoing basis.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeit wurde anerkannt \u2013 Bertelsmann Stiftung weist Wernickes Kritik zur\u00fcck|date={{date|2007-05-23|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\n=== Social welfare cuts ===\nIn 2007, the trade union ver.di terminated its cooperation with the Bertelsmann Stiftung. The reason was that Arvato, a division of the Bertelsmann Group, declared the privatization of public services a strategic business area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.handelsblatt.com/mediawatcher/2007/10/15/bertelsmann-kampft-mit-boykott-von-verdi/|title=Bertelsmann k\u00e4mpft mit Boykott von Verdi|date={{date|2007-10-15|mdy}}|website=Medienwatcher|publisher=Handelsblatt|language=de|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|author=Hans-Peter Siebenhaar}}</ref> A corresponding motion was passed at the union's federal congress against the wishes of its federal governing board.<ref name=\"2007-10-31\">{{cite news|title=Beziehungen auf Eis gelegt: Verdi setzt Zusammenarbeit mit Bertelsmann aus|date={{date|2007-10-31|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung is the driving force behind privatizations and cuts to [[social welfare]] programs, critics claimed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die heimliche Regierung aus G\u00fctersloh|date={{date|2007-11-02|mdy}}|language=de|author=Rudolf Stumberger|newspaper=VDI Nachrichten}}</ref> This assessment was supported by participants at \"Das Schattenkabinett aus G\u00fctersloh\" (\"The Shadow Cabinet from G\u00fctersloh\"), a conference critical of Bertelsmann.<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Kritik schwillt weiter an|date={{date|2007-10-27|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische|author=Stefan Brams}}</ref> In addition to [[ver.di]], other participants included [[Association for the Taxation of Financial Transactions and for Citizens' Action|Attac]], [[Education and Science Workers' Union (Germany)|GEW]], [[IG Metall]] and the Otto Brenner Foundation.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kontrastreiches Programm: Bertelsmann-Kritiker kontra Gemeinn\u00fctzigkeit|date={{date|2007-10-30|mdy}}|language=de|author=Stefan Brams|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.taz.de/!5192664/|title=Eine Kasse f\u00fcr sich|date={{date|2007-10-29|mdy}}|access-date={{date|2016-10-01|mdy}}|page=17|language=de|newspaper=Die Tageszeitung|author=Daniel Bouhs}}</ref> The Bertelsmann Stiftung rejected the criticism from ver.di in particular as a \"misunderstanding,\"<ref name=\"2007-10-31\" /> saying that both sides were not that far apart in their views on social problems.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stiftung wirbt um Verdis Vertrauen|date={{date|2007-11-10|mdy}}|language=de|newspaper=Neue Westf\u00e4lische}}</ref>\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite book|title=Bertelsmann: Hinter der Fassade des Medienimperiums|publisher=Eichborn Verlag|year=2004|isbn=3-8218-5551-7|location=Frankfurt am Main|language=de|author=Frank B\u00f6ckelmann, Hersch Fischler}}\n* {{cite book|title=Die Kunst des Stiftens: 20 Perspektiven auf Stiftungen in Deutschland|publisher=Edition Pro Arte|year=2005|isbn=3-9805009-6-9|location=Berlin|pages=22\u201325|language=de|author=Ulrich Br\u00f6mmling}}\n* {{cite book|title=Bertelsmann: Ein globales Medienimperium macht Politik / Expansion als Bildungsdienstleister und politische Einflussnahme \u2013 internationale Perspektive|publisher=Anders Verlag|year=2006|isbn=3-939594-01-6|location=Hamburg|language=de|editor=Thomas Bart}}\n* {{cite book|title=Agenda Bertelsmann: Ein Konzern stiftet Politik|publisher=Papyrossa Verlag|year=2007|isbn=978-3-89438-372-5|location=K\u00f6ln|language=de|author=Werner Biermann, Arno Kl\u00f6nne}}\n* {{cite book|title=Netzwerk der Macht \u2013 Bertelsmann / Der medial-politische Komplex aus G\u00fctersloh|publisher=Bund demokratischer Wissenschaftlerinnen und Wissenschaftler|year=2007|isbn=978-3-939864-02-8|editor=Jens Wernicke |editor2=Torsten Bultmann|location=Marburg|language=de}}\n* {{cite book|title=Die Bertelsmann Stiftung im Institutionengef\u00fcge \u2013 Medienpolitik aus Sicht des \u00f6konomischen Institutionalismus|publisher=Nomos Verlag|year=2008|isbn=978-3-8329-3982-3|location=Baden-Baden|language=de|author=Regina Hannerer, Christian Steininger}}\n* {{cite book|title=Bertelsmannrepublik Deutschland: Eine Stiftung macht Politik|publisher=Campus Verlag|year=2010|isbn=978-3-593-39097-0|location=Frankfurt am Main|language=de|author=Thomas Schuler}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|bertelsmann-stiftung.de}}\n\n{{Coord|51|54|30|N|8|25|09|E|region:DE-NW_type:landmark|display=title}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bertelsmann Foundation}}\n[[Category:1977 establishments in West Germany]]\n[[Category:Advocacy groups in Germany]]\n[[Category:Bertelsmann]]\n[[Category:Foundations based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Political and economic research foundations]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks based in Europe]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Think tanks based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Think tanks established in 1977]]\n", "name_user": "Kai at BSt", "label": "safe", "comment": "annual report 2019, infobox", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bertelsmann_Stiftung"}
{"title_page": "Josef Schraner", "text_new": "{{short description|Swiss cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Josef Schraner\n| image         =\n| caption       =\n| fullname      =\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1929|4|5|df=yes}}\n| birth_place   = [[Mellikon]], Switzerland\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   =\n| discipline    =\n| role          =\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     =\n| proteam1      =\n| majorwins     =\n}}\n\n'''Josef Schraner''' (born 5 April 1929) is a Swiss [[cycling|cyclist]]. He competed in the [[Cycling at the 1952 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's individual road race|individual]] and [[Cycling at the 1952 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team road race|team road race]] events at the [[1952 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/sc/josef-schraner-1.html |title=Josef Schraner Olympic Results |accessdate=30 December 2012 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Schraner, Josef}}\n[[Category:1929 births]]\n[[Category:Possibly living people]]\n[[Category:People from Zurzach District]]\n[[Category:Swiss male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1952 Summer Olympics]]\n{{Switzerland-cycling-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Swiss cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Josef Schraner\n| image         =\n| caption       =\n| fullname      =\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1929|4|5|df=yes}}\n| birth_place   = [[Mellikon]], Switzerland\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   =\n| discipline    =\n| role          =\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyear